title: peanut brittle
directions: You will need a candy thermometer for this one.
Bring sugar, water and corn syrup to boil or 280° on candy thermometer.
Stir in peanuts.
Boil to 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
STIR QUICKLY!
Then pour in 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Let cool and break up.
Keep in sealed plastic Ziploc bags or a tight-fitting plastic pan with lid or it will get sticky.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and cook onion and mushrooms.
Stir in soups.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes. Yields 8 cups.

title: polish honey cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, whole egg and honey.
Add rest of dry ingredients with coffee.
When well mixed, fold in egg whites.
Bake in 350° oven in well-greased tube pan, 50 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Take sugar and milk; heat to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream and mix together, then add peanut butter.
Put into buttered pan.

title: chocolate bottom cupcakes(jesse's favorite!)
directions: In large bowl, combine in order, then mix with mixer.
Fill muffin cups 1/3 full of batter; drop 1 well rounded teaspoon of cream cheese mix in middle.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 18.

title: sausage-squash casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Slice squash; boil about 10 minutes, drain and chop coarsely.
Combine all ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate "wet" cake
directions: Combine sugar and sifted flour in mixer bowl.
Bring margarine, cocoa, shortening and water to boil in saucepan and pour over sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture in bowl.
Mix together (batter will be thin).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Saute the onions and celery.
Combine meat and soup.
Add all of the ingredients except the eggs.
Make alternate layers of meat mixture and sliced eggs.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: man's soup
directions: Drain oysters and save liquid.
Melt butter in large pot. Cook oysters 5 minutes or until edges curl.
Add salt, pepper, oyster liquid and cream.
Heat on medium until bubbles begin to form.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cooking time:
15 minutes.

title: summertime pasta salad
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar and flour, gradually stir in water and vinegar until smooth. Bring to a boil; cook and stir 2 minutes until thickened. Cool completely. Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions. Rinse with cold water and drain. Stir mayonnaise and mustard into dressing. In a large bowl combine remaining ingredients. Add pasta and dressing, toss to coat. Cover and chill until serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Brown beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Combine noodles, meat, sauce, spices and all but 3 tablespoons cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar real well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and thoroughly beat mixture until it is all the same texture.
Fold in the sour cream (mixing the batter very well).

title: lemon lush
directions: Cut shortening into flour (like pie dough); press into bottom of 11 x 7-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly; mix and spread on Second Layer while still warm.

title: bran muffins
directions: Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and remove from grease.
In small roaster or large casserole dish, combine hamburger, frozen vegetables, cream of mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Also mix in some Tater Tots.
On top of hot dish, place a layer of Tater Tots.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chess cake bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and egg.
The mixture will be more like a dough.
Spread the mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch size pan.
Set aside.
Mix in a blender or mixer, powdered sugar, eggs and cream cheese.
Pour the mixture of powdered sugar, eggs and cream cheese over the cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool before cutting into bars. The cake will fall; don't panic, it is suppose to!

title: rolls (yeast)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into muffin tin.
Bake until brown at 375°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch strips.
Brown on both sides in a greased skillet.
Cover with onion and peppers.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender. Serve over cooked rice.

title: turkey cheddar rice bake
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour and chicken bouillon.
Gradually stir in milk, stirring mixture until it comes to a boil.
Stir in turkey and mushrooms.
Arrange rice in a nonstick 8-inch baking pan.
Spoon turkey mixture over rice and sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet; add the garlic and onion and saut until the onions are transparent. Meanwhile, slice the squash and peel and cube the eggplant. Flour the pieces lightly. Add the squash, eggplant and green peppers to the skillet; cover and cook slowly about 30 minutes. Add the tomatoes and capers and simmer, uncovered, until the mixture is thick, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Serve hot or cold.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix a pack of yellow cake mix first.
Second, melt the stick of butter.
Put it in the mix and stir, then put in the eggs and beat it together, then put in flour and stir.
Put the baking powder in.
Put half of a cup of water and stir.
Put it in the pans and cut the stove on (about 250°).
Let them stay for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift cocoa, flour, salt and baking powder all together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour in tube pan, bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: burger bundles
directions: Mix beef with Pet milk and shape into patties.
Prepare the Stove Top dressing according to directions on box and place equal amounts of dressing on patties.
Form dressing around patties into large meatballs and place in pan.
Mix soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut off of lid from bread and hollow out, saving pieces to dip with.
Mix remaining ingredients together and fill bread.
Replace the lid.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Remove lid for last 15 minutes.
Place pieces of bread in broiler and brown; use to dip or use chips.

title: boiled custard(no cooking)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender or use a mixer.
Chill overnight.

title: dot's dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and 1 cup chopped nuts and line in a large pie plate.
Cook 15 minutes at 350° until brown.
Then cool.

title: creamy broccoli cheese dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in medium bowl. Serve with vegetable dippers and assorted crackers, if desired.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: chicken breasts,  french-style
directions: Pound chicken breasts with wooden mallet until about 1/4-inch thick.
Place ham and cheese on each.
Tuck in sides and roll up as for jelly roll. Skewer or tie securely. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown in butter.
Remove from skillet.
Place in shallow baking pan. Combine soup with wine and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine shortening and 1 cup of sugar.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, salt, milk and lemon peel.
Place in greased and floured pan; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake by box directions.
Bake and let cool.
Cut and crumble 1/2 in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix pudding and pour 1/2 on crumbled cake.
Mix glaze with strawberries and pour half in punch bowl.
Put half of the Cool Whip in bowl.
Repeat layering with remaining ingredients, ending with Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
You can also put some whole strawberries on top. This cake goes a long way.

title: marinated turkey (or chicken)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put turkey or chicken in marinade.
Put in fridge for at least 12 hours.
Take meat out and fry until done in frypan.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine the corn, eggs, flour and nutmeg in a bowl and mix well. Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot vegetable oil in a skillet. Fry until golden brown on both sides. Drain on paper towels.

title: cheerio munchies
directions: Cook butter, marshmallows and vanilla until melted.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Press into greased cookie sheet.
Cool and enjoy.

title: fresh fruit dip #2
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Serve with fresh fruit: bananas, grapes, melons, strawberries, peaches, nectarines, plums, etc.

title: deena's famous fudge
directions: Boil sugar
and
milk
together in a saucepan, stirring constantly with
a	wooden	spoon
until
it is on "soft ball" stage on
the
candy thermometer.
(Or, when a drop of mixture is placed in cup of cold water, it forms a ball.)

title: something simple casserole
directions: Microwave hot dog enough to take chill out.
Cut in slices.

title: texas bonbons
directions: Delicious no-cook candy morsels easy for children to make.

title: taco in a bowl
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until meat is brown; drain off fat. Add water, undrained tomatoes, undrained beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Ladle into 6 bowls and pass cheese, chips and sour cream to top each serving.

title: "mother-in-law surprise"
directions: Mix butter with 1/2 cup sugar; add graham cracker crumbs. Press in bottom of 11 x 8-inch pan.
Set aside.
Beat 1/2 cup sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Should be runny.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Top with pie filling.
Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add milk, butter and eggs.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Use any plain pastry recipe for crust.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Put meringue on top and bake in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can use coconut or pineapple instead of chocolate.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix together in a large bowl with other ingredients.
Store in airtight bowl in refrigerator. When ready to bake, use greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Dough will keep well for about 1 week.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk to combine the mixture.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions. Drain off 1/2 cup pineapple juice. Add sugar to pineapple. Boil 6 minutes. Let cool, then spread over cake. Make instant pudding according to directions and beat in cream cheese until smooth. Spread over pineapple layer. Slice bananas over pudding layer, then spread Cool Whip on next. Top with nuts, cherries and coconut.

title: chip casserole
directions: Layer a 9-inch pan with chips.
Heat chilli and pour over corn chips.
Then layer browned hamburger meat over chilli.
Heat corn, then drain and pour over hamburger meat.
Then sprinkle cheese on top and melt in oven.

title: serbian spinach
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Keeps warm well or may be frozen and baked later.

title: baked butternut squash
directions: Butter a 1-quart baking dish; set aside.
Position rack in center of oven and preheat to 350°.
Using food processor, slice squash thinly.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat. Add shallots and saute until softened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in squash; add salt, nutmeg and pepper to taste and cook 3 more minutes.
Transfer to prepared dish.
(Can be prepared ahead to this point; cover and chill.)
Bake covered for 45 minutes.
Add parsley and toss lightly.
Adjust seasoning.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add salt.
Pour soda into mashed bananas and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and flour.
Mix well.
Bake in a well-greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini soup
directions: For
fresh
herbs, use basil, tarragon, cilantro, thyme or oregano.
Saute
onion
in	butter and oil until soft.
Add broth, zucchini
and
herbs.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Transfer to	blender in batches and puree.
Season with pepper and garnish with lemon and/or dollop of yogurt.
Can be served warm or chilled.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Season pork chops to taste.
Brown in skillet.
Add potatoes to pork chops.
Mix soup and water and pour over pork chops. Cover and steam over medium heat for 1 hour.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar and brown sugar; add vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Sift together and add a little at a time, the flour, salt and soda.
Add and fold in oatmeal, chocolate bits and nuts. Heat oven to 350°.
Roll into small balls and cook until golden brown, about 10 minutes.

title: macadamia nut pie
directions: Put pastry in tart pans.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, until filling is set and golden brown.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cook until chicken and potatoes are done.

title: white castle's casserole
directions: Place hamburgers in casserole dish.
Cover with broccoli, then the melted cheese.
Crush the crackers and mix with the melted butter.
Place this on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Simmer the acini de pepe in boiling water 10 to 12 minutes and rinse after draining.
Drain the pineapple and mandarin orange juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Cook flour, sugar and eggs in the 1 1/2 cups juice until thickened.
Now combine the drained acini de pepe with the thickened mixture, the mandarin oranges, the pineapple, the lemon juice, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix and eat!

title: anadama bread
directions: Add boiling water to first four ingredients.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise until little more than double in size.
Form into 2 loaves; let rise again.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; cook over medium heat (stirring constantly), until mixture thickens.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell; top with meringue.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Bring to boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Do not stir!
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats, then coconut.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool. Enjoy!

title: strawberry slush
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: layered fish and mushroom stuffing bake
directions: Mix well the mushrooms, cheese, celery, onion, salt and pepper, bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons wine and 1 tablespoon melted butter.
In a shallow 8 x 18-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 the fillets.
Cover with the vegetable mixture.
Layer remaining fillets on top (crosswise from the bottom layer).
Salt and pepper to taste and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until fish is done.
Mix remaining wine with undiluted soup and heat.
Reserve 1/3 cup of this sauce and toss with the remainder of the noodles.
Serve with fish dish.
Cut into squares.

title: sweet-n-sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat, eggs, seasoning and crumbs.
Roll into balls.
Fry until brown.
Make sauce of jelly and chili sauce.
Simmer meatballs in sauce.

title: leftover roast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir milk into melted cheese spread. Stir in beef, vegetables, potatoes, 1/2 can French fried onions and the seasonings.
Bake in a glass 9 x 13-inch pan, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Top with Cheddar cheese; sprinkle on onions.
Bake, uncovered, until golden brown, about 3 minutes.

title: grilled red snapper
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add onions and saute until clear. Add garlic, lemon/lime juice, mustard, salt and pepper.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into balls the size of half dollars. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well with fork or spoon.
Chill and serve with any fruit chunks, grapes, bananas, apples, pineapple, etc.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix lightly.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May take a little longer.
Serve right away.

title: 10-minute dinner
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add soups, vegetables and 3/4 cup chow mein noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole or 9-inch square pan.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 400° (uncovered) for 10 minutes.

title: poor man's chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet; add celery and 1 cup water.
Simmer until celery is tender.
Blend cornstarch and remaining water.
Cook until thick.
Add salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Stir into beef mixture; add bean sprouts and steam slowly about 30 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove all seeds from peppers and grind well in a blender (or chop finely by hand).
Bring sugar, vinegar and ground peppers to a hard boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Certo and let stand 5 minutes.
Skim off top foam.
Add red or green food coloring if desired.
Pour into sterile jars and seal with hot wax.
Makes 18 (2-ounce) jars.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind Oreos in food processor or blender.
Mix pudding mix and milk (until pudding is thick) with mixer.
Set aside.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter.
Fold pudding mixture in with Cool Whip mixture (do not mix).
Then, in large bowl or flower pot, layer Oreos and batter, beginning and ending with Oreos.
The more layers, the better.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan over low heat. Stir in sour cream and flour. Fill ungreased muffin pans 2/3 full. Preheat oven to 375°. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 10 muffins.

title: last minute dessert
directions: Mix fruit and stir in pudding and Cool Whip.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish. Add sliced boiled eggs over this. Mix chicken broth, chicken soup and Veg-All (drained) and pour over chicken. Melt butter and mix flour and milk. Pour over chicken and vegetable mixture. Bake at 375° until crust is brown.
Batter will form its own crust.

title: chocolate chip cream squares
directions: Slice one roll of cookies 1/8-inch thick.
Layer over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla (set cream cheese at room temperature for 1 hour).
Spread mixture over bottom layer of cookies.
Slice second roll of cookies and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool first, then cut in 1-inch squares.

title: family meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients lightly, but well. Shape into a loaf.
Put in a shallow baking pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow loaf to stand about 5 or 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: go-fer cookies
directions: Melt
2 sticks margarine and pour over first 6 ingredients. Mix
by hand and shape into small balls.
Melt 1/2 cake paraffin and
small
package chocolate chips.
Dip cookies into chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, molasses, salt, flour and hot water. Add white flour to mixture alternately with yeast water.
Let dough raise.
Knead down.
Raise again; put into pans (will make a couple of large and 3 medium loaves).
Raise.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is a very sticky, heavy dough and will stick to your hands.
It will take longer than most bread doughs to raise (probably at least 2 hours in between each raising).
It should crack and snap when you knead.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In saucepan, melt over low heat shortening; take from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Set aside to cool.
Into cooled sugar and shortening, stir egg; add and blend well flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 25 minutes, only until a toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
Do not overbake!
Cool in pan and cut into squares.
Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake according to package.
Pour liqueur over after it is baked.
Tear cake into small pieces or cut into small squares. Prepare pudding as directed.
Put layer cake in large glass bowl or trifle bowl.
Put a layer of pudding, layer of crushed Heath bars, layer of nuts and layer of Cool Whip.
Continue layers until bowl is full, Cool Whip being the last layer.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours. Makes 2 big bowls of dessert.

title: ham loaf balls
directions: Form into balls.
Place in a long cake pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° to brown slightly.
Remove from oven and turn meatballs in the pan.
Return to the oven for another 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain off hot grease.
Makes about 40 meatballs.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add milk, salad oil and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Add all ingredients and stir well.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.
Stir again before serving.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Pierce box of broccoli with fork.
Place on a paper towel. Cook, uncovered, in microwave oven for 5 minutes at High setting. Drain well.
Combine drained broccoli, soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Cover with an all-glass lid or plastic wrap.
Set aside.
Reserve onions. Microwave on High for 5 to 10 minutes, until hot.
Garnish with onions.
Serve.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Cream first
four
ingredients	together.
Add	rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Form
into balls the size of walnuts. Drop on greased cookie
sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until
edges are slightly browned.
Dust with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: mom's molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well; drop by spoonfuls on ungreased sheets. Bake at 375° approximately 10 minutes.

title: microwave cinnamon fold-ups
directions: Combine egg whites and sugar and mix well.
Stir in, one at a time, the other ingredients, except butter; mix well.
Melt butter. Add batter to melted butter and beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a lightly greased baking sheet (compatible for microwave). Microwave at Full power for 3 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute.
Curl cookie while warm.
The top of the cookie will be the outside; the under part will be folded inwards.
(Can add a message when folding.)

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Sift together baking powder, salt and flour.
Pour dry mix into eggs.
Use a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 90 minutes at 325°, start in cold oven.

title: nut butter crunch
directions: Melt butter over low heat in pan.
Add sugar and stir until melted.
Add water and syrup.
Continue cooking over low heat until syrup dropped in cold water is brittle (320°).
Don't overcook.
Remove from heat.
Pour on greased platter.
This should be thin.
Cool until hardened; melt chocolate over hot water.
Spread on crunch.
Sprinkle nuts over the top and pat in. Break into pieces.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Blend flour and sugar, add mustard and mix.
Then add eggs and mix.
Then add vinegar.
Cook these ingredients until thick over low heat.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise.
Mix until smooth. May add more mayonnaise if necessary.

title: oatmeal krispies
directions: Cream the sugars and Crisco until well creamed.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well, then add flour, soda, salt, oatmeal and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: easy eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Spread both sides with mayo.
Dip in cornflake crumbs or cracker crumbs.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine oats and milk.
Set aside until milk is absorbed.
In a medium bowl mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add margarine, egg and bananas to the oat mixture.
Mix well then add dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
You can grease and flour your muffin tins or use cupcake liners.

title: prosciutto bread
directions: Place 1 slice of Prosciutto and one slice of tomato on each piece of bread.
Top with a slice of the cheese and a sprinkle of the parsley.
Place on a cookie sheet and broil until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: zesty italian cheeseball
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into a ball.
Cover ball with dried parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Blend together flour and salt; stir in mixture.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat well the eggs. Add sugar and shortening. Stir in milk. Add flour and vanilla. Mix well. Chill dough for 2 hours. Heat fat in deep pot. Roll out and cut out doughnuts with doughnut cutter. Fry until golden brown in hot 370 to 380 degree oil. Drain. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hamburger rice pie
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, seasonings and 1/2 can Hunt's tomato sauce.
Spread in greased 9-inch pie pan, pushing mixture in
sides of pan to form an edge.
Mix rice, cheese and remaining sauce.
Place in meat shell.

title: preacher's meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, sausage, Wheaties, onions and eggs thoroughly. Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce into mixture generously.
Place in loaf pan and spread catsup over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: steak fingers
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl (except egg).
Beat egg in separate bowl.
Dip steak in egg, then in flour and spices.

title: snow cream
directions: Beat egg white until fluffy.
Stir in sugar, milk and vanilla. Keep mixture cold while you hustle out and scoop up the whitest, fluffiest snow you can find.
Gently stir snow into flavoring and serve at once.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish, salt and pepper. Mix soup and milk, pour over chicken. Bake at 350° covered for 1 hour, uncovered for 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with mashed potatoes and vegetable.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix dressing, onion soup mix and preserves in a blender or food processor.
Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder or salt. Pour dressing mix over chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour. Cover the first half of baking.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: In a large bowl combine butter, margarine, vanilla and salt on low speed of mixer about 1 minute.
Blend well.
Add flour and lightly spoon flour into measuring cup level.
Gradually add flour at low speed until just combined.
Stir in chopped nuts.

title: shanty beans
directions: Cut bacon into 1 1/2-inch pieces and fry.
Drain 1/2 of the grease.
Drain beans and add with brown sugar to bacon and grease. Cook for 1/2 hour until thick.
Serves 6.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat until done; drain grease.
Add chili seasoning, then stir.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, noodles, peas, pimento and chicken in a 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: In a blender, place juice from lemons (with pulp), water and ice.
Blend on high speed until ice is crushed.
Add sugar until it suits your taste.
A great summer thirst quencher!

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter and Crisco; add sugars.
Beat for 5 minutes on medium speed of mixer after the sugars are mixed with butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Do not overbeat.
Beat only until yolks cannot be seen or disappear.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Start in a cold oven.
After oven light goes off, bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Set oven at 325°.
When you take cake out, let it sit in pan for about 5 minutes on cake rack before removing to plate.

title: crock-pot party beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease. Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook for 3 hours on high or 5 hours on low.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla together until smooth and put into prepared pie shell.
Put crushed pineapple on cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip, drizzle with chocolate syrup and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
This is a really fast, easy and delicious dessert.

title: strawberry tea punch
directions: In pitcher, pour water over tea bags; brew 4 minutes.
Remove tea bags and stir in sugar, lemonade and strawberries.
Serve over ice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and milk (alternate flour and milk, start with flour and end with milk).
Add cake mix last.
This
makes
two
cakes or a very large sheet cake.

title: cheesy reuben casserole
directions: In a shallow casserole, layer the kraut, tomatoes, dressing, butter, corned beef and cheese.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: marshmallow roll
directions: Blend milk and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cream.
Shape into a roll and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Cut roll and garnish with whipped cream.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Blend butter and flour in a saucepan until smooth.
Gradually add milk and half and half, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in small amount of water.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Cook until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and serve hot.

title: spunky spareribs
directions: Place ribs, meaty side down, in shallow roasting pan.
Roast in 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Turn ribs and roast 30 minutes more.
Drain off fat.

title: squash gratin(gratin de courge; serves 6)
directions: Over very low heat, melt 4 tablespoons butter in a large earthenware poelon or heavy saute pan.
Add the onion, squash, salt, pepper and coriander and sweat, covered, for about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon and shaking the poelon from time to time.
Preheat the oven to 375°.
Sprinkle the squash with the flour; stir and adjust the heat to medium.
Add the milk, a little at a time, stirring until the squash is bound in a thin sauce.
Turn the heat very low again and leave to simmer gently, uncovered, for about 15 minutes, stirring from time to time.
Stir in the cream and mint; empty the mixture into a buttered gratin dish.
Smooth the surface; sprinkle with cheese. Grate over bread crumbs; scatter the surface with shavings of butter and bake for 30 minutes, or until the surface is golden.

title: buttermilk pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Pour into pie crust.
Bake in oven on 325° for 1 hour.

title: date roll
directions: Roll graham crackers fine.
Save 5 crackers to roll for outside of loaf.
Cut all ingredients and mix with crumbs and cream.
Shape into roll and roll in crumbs of five or 6 crackers. Put in wax paper in refrigerator until ready to use, at least overnight.

title: savory rice
directions: Brown rice in butter in skillet.
Pour into casserole dish; add consomme and sliced onions.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk.
Store in covered dish in refrigerator.
Will keep for days.
Roll out, cut and bake at 350° when desired.

title: meatball sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients except rolls.
Make sandwiches on hard rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
If refrigerated, bake for 45 minutes. If frozen, bake for 1 hour (then check).

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crumble pretzel sticks and mix with melted oleo and sugar. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes. Blend cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread mixture over cooled pretzel crust.
Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour jello mixture over cheese mixture and let set.

title: chinese chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix together, except potato chips and almonds; place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with the crushed potato chips and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well. Roll into balls and brown in a small amount of margarine.
After browned good, drain fat out and add some water and bouillon cube (1), more if more water is used.
Simmer 1/2 hour and make thickening for gravy. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Roll into balls; flatten with fork.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.
Yield:
120 cookies.

title: spring garden dip
directions: Dice all vegetables very fine and mix ingredients.
Chill and serve with carrot and celery strips, cauliflower, cucumber and bell pepper strips.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Heat the juice.
Add Jell-O and stir.
Melt marshmallows in hot juice.
When Jell-O and marshmallows are melted, add fruit and fold in whipped cream. Add pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set. Serves 8.

title: bird's nests
directions: Melt chocolate chips; add peanut butter. Crush shredded wheat biscuits and stir in with peanut butter and chocolate.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper.
Indent to make nest.
Put 3 small jelly beans in each.
Chill.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix
sugar
and
flour	together
and stir in pineapple juice. Mix pineapple, cheese, melted butter and sugar together.
Bake in	a
large casserole dish at 350° for 20 minutes. Lower temperature
to 300° and bake 20 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and
top
with
cracker crumbs. Return to oven long enough to heat
crumbs.
Serve
warm.
May
halve
recipe for small casserole.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa good.
Add milk.
Stir until blended good, then cook over low heat, stirring continuously until thick.
Add margarine; mix in good.
Recipe can be halved for less gravy.
Serve over biscuit.

title: layered lime jello
directions: Heat 2 cups of water to boiling.
Dissolve jello; add 2 cups cold water, pineapple and nuts.
Let set until firm in flat dish. When cold, cream together cream cheese and whipped Dream Whip; spread on jello layer.
Cook juices, flour, sugar and eggs until thick.
Cool, then spread on top of cream cheese layer.

title: fantastic brisket
directions: Score meat with the grain.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan, fat side up.
Mix chili sauce, Coke or beer and onion soup.
Pour sauce over meat, cover with foil and bake at 275° for 3 hours. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, carve into slices against the grain, bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: strawberry jam nut loaf(yields 2 loaves)
directions: Cream butter or margarine, vanilla, sugar and lemon extract together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, salt and soda; add to first mixture.
Combine strawberry jam, sour cream or milk and nuts.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: snow punch
directions: Beat mashed bananas, lemon juice and sugar.
Chill thoroughly. When ready to serve, put chilled banana mix into punch bowl.
Pour cream over.
Slowly pour in Sprite.
Float spoonfuls of lemon sherbet on punch.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Serves 40.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Prepare meat.
Fry hamburger with potato.
Season with garlic, salt, pepper, cumin and chili powder.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer until creamy.
Pour over corn chips and top with lettuce, tomato and onion.

title: herb artichoke spread
directions: Stir together ingredients until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with toasted bread cutouts.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix cake and bake according to directions.
Then mix 1/2 cup milk with softened cream cheese.
Beat 5 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk to that.
Then put pudding in mixture and pour over cake. Then put crushed pineapple over that.
Top with Dream Whip.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix softened butter, flour and 2 tablespoons of 10x sugar. Press into a square pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cream butter with 10x sugar and eggs.
Spread over cooled mixture in pan.
Top with crushed pineapple and whipping cream.
Leave in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: frozen stuffed peppers
directions: Add last 8 ingredients all together.
Stuff pepper halves and freeze.

title: marzettie
directions: Brown onion and celery.
Add undiluted soups and cubed cheese. Stir until blended and cheese is melted.
Brown meat and combine with sauce.
Cook noodles until tender.
Drain and add to mix mixture.
Place all in a large casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: diabetic pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Beat
eggs
whites
until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat
until
stiff.
Add
sugar, two tablespoons at a time,
beating
after each addition. Stir in vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls (bite size) on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Place in oven preheated to 350° and turn off immediately.
Do
not
open
oven
door
for at least 8 hours. Carefully remove cookies from foil.
Makes 40 to 50 cookies.

title: fruited ice
directions: Mix all together and place in freezer.
Stir 2 or 3 times while freezing.
Set out about 30 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter sundae sauce
directions: In heavy 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, warm brown sugar, half and half and honey to boiling, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Serve sauce warm over ice cream, pancakes or waffles, or refrigerate and reheat slowly, stirring constantly, for later use. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: beef fajitas with rice
directions: Prepare the rice as directed on the package, omitting the margarine and salt.
Heat the oil in a large skillet.
Add the meat, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until meat is browned clear through.
Add the peppers and cook, stirring slowly, until tender. Stir in the water, soy sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in the lime juice.
Serve over the rice.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute garlic, onion, bell pepper, celery, sausage and oleo in heavy pan for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, shrimp, water and seasoning to taste.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Serves 8 generously.
Be prepared to share recipe!

title: great salmon steaks
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in small bowl.
Brush 1/2 the mix over fish.
Marinate fish up to 6 hours in refrigerator.
Place fish on grill.
Grill 5 minutes.
Turn and brush with the rest of marinade.
Grill until fish flake easily.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until thickens.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until firm, about 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: sweet smoked sausage
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl; set aside.
In small pan warm apple jelly and vinegar over low heat until smooth.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Transfer to 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Place in 400°
oven and cook 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. In large skillet over medium-high heat, saute sliced sausage until lightly browned.
When vegetables are tender, arrange drained sausage on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: crazy corn crunch
directions: Spread popped corn, broken pecans and peanuts on a cookie sheet.
In a pan bring to a boil the rest of the ingredients. Stir constantly; cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until it turns a light caramel color.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Then pour over corn and nuts.
Spread out to cool and dry.
Then break into chunks.
Stir
in tightly closed container.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine meal and soda in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil; mix well.
Stir in cheese, onions, corn and peppers.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and heat 10-inch iron skillet in oven.
Pour batter in hot skillet.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: manner's strawberry pie
directions: Put in pan and boil the cornstarch, sugar and water until clear.
Add the Jell-O.
Let cool.
Cut berries in half.
Fold strawberries into thickening Jell-O.
Pour into baked and cooled pie shell.
Keep refrigerated.

title: m&m drops
directions: Melt white chocolate in a double boiler, then put half of the chocolate in a bowl.
Add plain M&M's; mix.
Drop this mixture onto wax paper.
With remaining chocolate, put in peanut M&M's; mix.
Drop onto wax paper with a teaspoon; let set about 30 minutes.

title: cream of squash soup
directions: Combine oil and oleo in large Dutch oven. Add onion and garlic; saute until tender. Stir in squash and chicken broth; cover and simmer until squash is tender. Spoon 1/3 of squash mixture into blender; process until smooth. Repeat with remaining mixture. Return squash mixture to Dutch oven. Stir in half and half, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until well heated. Garnish with parsley. Yields 10 cups.

title: cajun chili
directions: Combine the ground chuck and onion in large soup pot.
Cook over medium to medium high heat until meat has browned.
Add remaining ingredients (including the seasoning packet from the beans and rice mix) and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook covered for about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
If you like your chili hotter, simply add more Cajun seasoning.

title: angle salad
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, beaten eggs and vinegar.
Cook 2 minutes or until thick.
This makes the sauce.

title: val's shrimp quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion and garlic in oil 1 minute. Add vegetables and stir for 2 minutes on medium heat.
Remove vegetables from pan and saute shrimp in reserved liquid until pink.
Drain shrimp.
(Some people like them chopped.)
Place shrimp, vegetables and cheese in pie shell.
Whip eggs with cream, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over shrimp, vegetables and cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375° or until eggs are cooked firm.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Make into straws or roll into balls.
Press with a fork to make a cheese wafer.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown.
If making into straws cut while warm.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix.
Let rise.
Make shell and bake lightly before adding sauce.

title: loraine's fudge cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix in with sugar/oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with each addition.
Add nuts.

title: chicken sauce piquante
directions: Brown chicken in oil, remove chicken, add onions, green onions, green pepper and garlic to pan and brown.
Sprinkle flour over onions and stir, add remaining ingredients and chicken. Cover with water and cook until chicken is done, about 1 hour.
I debone and skin mine before serving, but you don't have too. Serve over rice.
Better the second day!

title: chile cheese log
directions: Beat seasoning, cream cheese and salsa.
Shape into log and top with nuts and cheese.
Chill until firm.

title: copper pennies
directions: Wash and peel carrots.
Cook until barely tender.
Drain. Combine rest of ingredients and pour over hot carrots. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: hot turkey sandwiches
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook carrots, onions, celery and thyme until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in gravy.
Heat to boiling.
Add turkey.
Heat through stirring occasionally.
Divide turkey and gravy mixture evenly among bread slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poor boy chuck
directions: Brown chuck roast in hot oil on stove.
Place roast in baking pan; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour cream of mushroom soup from can to top of roast.
Spread.
Separate onion slices into rings. Lay over top of roast.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake in 325° oven for 3 hours.
Remove foil.
Mix horseradish to taste with sour cream. Spread over roast (scrape onions off first).
Broil under broiler until bubbly.
Serve with rice or boiled potatoes.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons margarine and set aside.
Cook spinach according to label directions and drain well.
Add onion, Muenster cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg to spinach.
Spoon into 6 cup baking dish.

title: chocolate-nut brownies(for diabetics)
directions: Combine margarine, sugar substitute, vanilla and eggs.
Sift together cocoa, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add mixtures until well blended.
(Do not overmix.)
Stir in nuts.
Pour in 8-inch square pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen coconut pies
directions: Toast coconut and nuts with butter until a dark brown.
To the soft cream cheese, add milk and beat until smooth, then fold Cool Whip.
Layer the cream and milk mixture with caramel, then nuts, then repeat until pie shells are full.
Freeze pies for 2 hours. Serve pies frozen.

title: can-can chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° until light brown and bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Blend sugar with cake mix.
Add oil, sour cream and eggs. Pour 1/2 of mixture into a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans.
Add remainder of batter on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry cake dessert
directions: Mix together cherry pie filling and tart cherries.
Put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle on dry box of yellow cake mix, evenly.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Melt margarine and pour over all. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
May use other fruit.
Easy to make and no mess.

title: almost lasagna
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain fat.
Stir in sauce and water; bring to a boil.
Add noodles; cook until tender.
Mix in bowl cottage cheese, parsley flakes, salt, oregano, garlic salt and egg.
Layer ground beef mixture and cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese in baking dish, 9 x 12-inch.
Add mushrooms if you like. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry until crisp.
Remove bacon and measure fat. Add half as much vinegar.
Add onion, parsley, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well and heat through.
Pour over potatoes and mix lightly. Cover dish until flavors are blended.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Remove from oven, poke holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake and 1 jar of Smuckers caramel ice cream topping.
Refrigerate over night.
Spread cool whip over cake and crush 2 heath bars on top of cool whip before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Toss chicken with flour.
In saucepan, cook carrots, onion, celery, poultry seasoning and pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, chicken and potatoes.
Pour into pastry.
Top with other pastry.
Sprinkle top lightly with poultry seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together and press on 2 pizza pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine bacon, celery and onion in a 5-quart casserole. Microwave on High until bacon is crisp and vegetables are tender, 4 to 6 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots and 1/4 cup water.
Cover and microwave on High until potatoes are tender, 12 to 15 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.
Blend in flour.
Stir in vegetable juice, water, peas, salt and pepper.
Cover and microwave on High until soup is thickened and peas are heated through, 8 to 10 minutes.
If using oven other than Sharp Carousel, stir after half the cooking time.

title: stilton-stuffed mushrooms(yield: 8 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a large baking sheet with aluminum foil.
Lightly butter both sides of bread, using 4 Tbsp. of the butter; arrange on prepared baking sheet.
Bake 5 minutes, turning once, or until lightly browned on both sides.
Remove from oven and set aside.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut off stems from mushrooms and wash well.
Chop the stems and cook in olive oil with onion and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add anchovies, parsley, salt and
pepper and cook 5 minutes longer over high heat.
Remove from stove; add bread slice and egg and mix together until smooth.
Fill each mushroom cap with stuffing, rounding stuffing up on top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, then with oil and place in greased baking pan in hot oven (400°) for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rolled oats cake
directions: Mix butter and sugars, then add eggs.
Mix together dry ingredients, then add to the butter and sugar mixture.
Add in water, 1 cup at a time.
Batter is very thin.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or two loaf pans.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes. May top with coconut and pecan icing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add melted butter, sour cream, corn and cornbread mix.
Bake in greased casserole dish until done at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: beef and cheese pinwheels
directions: Cook butter and onion.
Combine egg, milk, 1 1/2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix in cornflakes and meat.
Pat meat into a 6 x 10-inch rectangle on a piece of wax paper.
Combine onion, remaining Worcestershire sauce and cheese; spread over meat.
Roll as for jelly roll.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Blend in salt, soda and vanilla.
Add Crisco and flour.
Add chocolate morsels; 1 cup of walnuts or pecans is optional.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheets for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: onion au gratin
directions: Mix onion which has been cooked, drained and chopped, with 3 1/2 cups cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and cool. Mix all ingredients together except salad dressing and toss.
Just before serving, add salad dressing.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain grease.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, tomato paste and water.
Cover and simmer until noodles are cooked.
Cook noodles according to package directions. (Add a little oil to keep from sticking.)
Drain and rinse.
Mix cheeses.

title: hot apple cider punch
directions: Heat cider, sugar, cloves and allspice.
Can be placed in pan with cider (or put in a tea ball).
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Strain punch (if not using tea ball).
Pour into punch bowl.
Float oranges studded with cloves in punch.
Makes 32 servings.

title: lu's chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except the potato chips in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Cover with the potato chips.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: buttermilk refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in melted shortening.
Combine dry ingredients in a small bowl.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk to yeast mixture; mix well. Turn dough out on a well floured surface; knead gently until dough can be handled.
Shape dough into a ball; place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover dough and refrigerate until needed (dough will keep 1 week).
Let rise. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: salsa, cheese and chips
directions: Warm cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and salsa together.
Serve with chips.

title: lunch box salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut, sprouts, corn and pimento in large bowl. Cook and add celery, green pepper, carrots and onion.
Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar, oil and water in saucepan.
Pour hot dressing over the vegetable mixture and stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt margarine, stir in cracker crumbs until well coated. Press 2/3 or mixture into bottom of 9 x 13 dish.
Save remaining crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Spread pie filling evenly over crumbs. In mixing bowl, put 2 envelopes of Dream Whip, cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Beat until creamy and thick.
Spread over pie filling.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together flour and salt. Cut in shortening until fine. Add milk and water. Makes 2 crusts. Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate in a small bowl over hot water; cool.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Top out with excess flour. Sift flour and baking soda onto wax paper.
Beat butter until soft in large bowl; add brown sugar and eggs.
Beat with mixer at high speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and cooled melted chocolate.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with sour cream beating well with a wooden spoon after each addition until batter is smooth.
Stir in boiling water.
Pour into cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until center springs back when gently pressed.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple with juice and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved well.
Cool.
Stir in buttermilk.
Add Cool Whip, oranges and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Let set overnight.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, except steak, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add steak, turn to coat, cover.
Refrigerate 5 hours or longer, turning occasionally.
Remove steak from marinade, reserve mixture.
Grill 4-inches from red hot coals or broil 4-inches from heat source, 12 to 14 minutes, until medium rare, turning once. Heat marinade in small saucepan.
Serve steak thinly sliced, across the grain.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
In crock-pot on low, add all ingredients.
Stir well and cook for about 1 1/2 hours or until mixture is smooth.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chip dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Put ground beef and onion in crock-pot and add remaining ingredients; heat until cheese is all melted, stirring occasionally.
Serve with round tortilla chips.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery and onion. Add salt and pepper. Chill overnight. Immediately before serving, stir in mayonnaise, mandarin oranges, grapes, pineapple chunks (if desired) and pecans. Mix well.

title: opal's seven layered salad
directions: Break lettuce into small pieces and place in large casserole dish.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: ribbon salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix lime Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add 1 1/4 cups cold water.
Refrigerate until it jells.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pineapple-buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and stir until combined. Fold in whipped topping and pecans.
Spoon into dish and chill until firm.
Cut salad into squares to serve.
(Use a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.)
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Good choice for potluck suppers.

title: nut caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in large heavy saucepan.
Boil, stirring occasionally until syrup is very thick (310° on a candy thermometer).
Add margarine and slowly stir in evaporated milk. Stir constantly.
Cook rapidly to firm ball stage (246°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
If mixture curdles, beat a minute or two. Add nuts and pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch square cake pan. Let stand until cool.
Cut and wrap individually in wax paper. Keeps well for 3 months.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high 5 minutes and add sugar and pumpkin.
Stir together spices and flour.
Spread on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Top with finely chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn on towel with confectioners sugar.
Roll up cake and towel together.
Cool well before putting filling on.

title: granny smith's molasses cookies
directions: Mix oil and 1 cup of sugar thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients. Add to mixture.
Drop by tablespoon or form small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve packages of Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in orange sherbet.
Add mandarin oranges.
Pour into serving dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: salisbury steak with peppers and onions
directions: In skillet over medium heat, melt butter and saute onions and peppers until tender, stirring.
Remove onion mixture to platter, draining oil in pan.
Mix hamburger meat, egg, oatmeal, flour, salt and pepper.
Form into patties.
Cook patties over medium-high heat in same skillet until done.
Place patties on platter with onion mixture.
Into skillet, stir flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Add water, catsup and soy sauce; cook until mixture thickens and pour over patties.

title: spinach and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and spinach and drain.
Blend rice and spinach with remaining ingredients.
Oil casserole dish and sprinkle with some bread crumbs.
Add mixture evenly and sprinkle top generously with more bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: sand tart cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add flour, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Form into 1/2-inch balls, then squash flat on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: 5 layer banana cake
directions: Mix and pour into an 8 x 11-inch pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add eggs, one at a time (beating often).
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Combine the Smeita and 3 teaspoons sugar; pour over top.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Cool and serve.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Spread the layers with the mayo, sour cream and sugar.
Let set overnight in refrigerator or 1 1/2 hours. Before serving add tomatoes, boiled eggs, bacon and Parmesan cheese. Toss lightly.

title: twice fried potatoes
directions: Slice the potatoes thinly.
Add olive oil (1/8 cup) to a heated nonstick frying pan.
Add crushed garlic to pan along with the potatoes.
Make sure the oil in the pan is adequate to coat the potatoes.
Fry the potatoes until lightly browned on both sides.
After lightly browned, remove the potatoes from the pan and let them cool completely.
After cool, reheat pan; add additional oil (1/8 cup) and cook the potatoes again on both sides until nicely browned and tender.
Salt to taste and serve.

title: lemon pepper steak rolls
directions: Pat steaks dry with paper towel.
Sprinkle both sides with grated lemon rind, lemon juice and pepper.	Cover and let marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Heat butter and oil in heavy large skillet.
Remove steaks from pan, shaking off the lemon juice; but don't blot.
Reserve marinade.
Add steaks to pan with butter and oil; saute over medium to high heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until done to your liking.	Remove steaks to heated platter and keep warm. Sprinkle with salt.
Add reserved lemon marinade and onion to pan; heat for 1 minute over high heat, stirring. Then add cornstarch blending well.
Add cream and Cognac or Brandy, if used.
Boil until sauce is smooth and thickened. Pour sauce over steaks and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: jasmine's creation
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to box directions. While hot, stir in corn and tuna.
Easy and yummy!

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, and add slowly sugar and vanilla. Spread meringue on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 300°.
Remove paper and cut in half while hot.
Makes 2 layers.

title: garlic spread
directions: Stir ingredients together and use.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Barely cover with water and cook until tender first 5 ingredients; drain.
Place in casserole dish; add butter.
Add soup mixed with evaporated milk.
Mix well with vegetables.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with grated cheese.
Heat in oven until bubbly.

title: fudge sauce icing
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of double boiler or on low heat.
Gradually stir in sugar.
Add milk slowly and blend well. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Pour over ice cream or cake.

title: sangria soul style
directions: Place sliced fruit
into
a
very large pitcher or jug. Mix sugar and
brandy
together until sugar dissolves and pour over fruit.
Let stand
at
room temperature for 1 hour.
Pour in red wine and lemon juice;
stir and let stand another hour. Just before serving, add ice cubes and soda water;
stir until thoroughly chilled and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brunch ham muffins
directions: Spread ham on muffin halves.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place on baking sheet.
Beat egg yolks, mustard, salt, pepper and Tabasco until thick and lemony.
Beat whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into yolk mixture.
Spoon onto muffins.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chow-chow relish
directions: Combine chopped vegetables; sprinkle with salt. Let stand 4 to 6 hours in a cool place. Drain well.

title: crusty cheese rings
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine flour and butter.
Cut butter into flour until slightly smaller than peas.
Mix in cream and vinegar with fork.
Stir in cheese, distributing evenly; form dough into ball.
Roll dough out on lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into rings, using doughnut cutter.
Place rings and centers (holes) on ungreased baking sheet 1-inch apart. Chill for 30 minutes.
Brush tops with egg white.
Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: duke blue devils chicken wings
directions: Toss chicken wings in sauce (set aside a portion of sauce for dipping before tossing wings).
Bake in 425° oven 45 minutes or until done.
Serve with sauce, celery and Blue cheese dip.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and salt.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Combine oatmeal, coconut, chocolate chips and Rice Krispies with flour and add to creamed mixture, slowly stirring in by hand.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry mold
directions: Drain cherries; reserve 3/4 cup syrup.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add reserved syrup.
Gradually add to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Put into oiled 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until almost set.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cold water and chill until partially set.
Fold in cherries.
Pour over molded layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold, surround with lettuce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: date loaf
directions: Let sugar and milk come to a boil.
Add dates.
Cook until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a ball.
Take off heat and add oleo and nuts.
Beat until thick.
Pour on clean damp cloth and roll up log style.
When cloth is dry, slice and eat.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Soak tortillas in chicken broth until wilted; reserve broth. Place tortillas in greased 2-quart baking dish, covering sides and bottom.
Combine chicken, onion, chili powder and garlic salt; place mixture over tortillas.
Mix remaining chicken broth with milk, flour and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Add chilies and tomatoes and top with grated cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: aunt jalia's light yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, adding 1 teaspoon of the sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cupcake brownies
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chocolate; cool for 10 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla and chocolate mixture; stir in flour and nuts.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: brown sugar pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in egg/milk mixture.
Coat with Ritz crackers. Brown in hot grease.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top with 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Cream well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Mix flour mixture and sugar mixture together.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese beef ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Chip in blender the beef.
Mix together.
Add chopped green onions and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Combine and shape into ball and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: squash cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until brown.
Can be frozen, uncooked.

title: granny's cheese ball
directions: Mix together; form into ball.
Roll in nuts and refrigerate. Great with assorted crackers.

title: chocolate yogurt melts
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (350°).
Combine cake mix, yogurt, egg and margarine in a large bowl; beat until blended.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Garnish with walnut halves (optional).
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until cookies are set.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 7 dozen.
Each cookie contains 49 calories.

title: virginia salad
directions: Let Jell-O set until thick but not firm.
Let cheese set at room temperature.
Beat cream cheese into Jell-O, then add rest of ingredients. Chill.

title: clams in spicy tomato sauce
directions: In a large pot, saute the onion and garlic in oil until the onion is wilted.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, paprika, wine, parsley, chili peppers and pepper.
Cover and cook 10 minutes. Add clams.
Cover and cook until clams open.
Serve as an appetizer or over linguini as a main dish.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake until set, about 50 minutes, at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese together; add milk, vanilla and pudding.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Place in layers, starting with cookies and end with cookies.
Use a big flowerpot or bowl.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add to this one egg at a time, continuing to mix.
Crunch vanilla wafers and add to mixture.
Then add pecans, milk and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix and heat the sugar and milk until milk coats spoon (just before boiling).
Combine the eggs, milk and Clark bars and mix with the hot mixture slowly, blending well.
Finish filling can with milk.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Put slaw, almonds, sunflower seeds and noodles in large bowl. Sprinkle seasoning packet over ingredients.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over slaw mix.
Toss well.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Place whole cucumbers in a crock, covering with boiling water. Allow to stand 24 hours.
Drain and repeat this process with boiling water for 3 more days (4 days in all).

title: chicken and peppers
directions: Cook and stir green peppers, onion and garlic in oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat until peppers are almost tender.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until chicken is done, about 8 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges. Serves 4.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken breast and place in baking dish. Coat each piece with salad dressing and sprinkle with lemon juice. Place 1 Tbsp. butter on each chicken breast. Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: peanut corn flake candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes and stir until covered well with syrup mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on a buttered pan. Cool.
Very good.

title: frost on the pumpkin pie(no bake pumpkin pie - this is delicious)
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer and mix on high speed until all blended. Pour into shell. Place in refrigerator and chill several hours. Put some more Cool Whip to decorate the pie in rings around the pie and in between sprinkle chopped nuts. Place some whole pecans on the Cool Whip to decorate (or other nuts). Serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine soup, milk and pepper in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish; mix well. Stir in beans and 1/2 of onions. Bake 10 minutes; stir. Sprinkle with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes or until hot and onions are golden.

title: vegetable delight
directions: Partially cook the spinach (1/2 the recommended time).
Saute onion in butter.
Combine spinach, artichoke hearts, oil, bread crumbs, onion and cheese in a casserole type dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: skillet tomato beef pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and drain well. Brown beef and onion in large skillet while pasta is cooking, then drain. Add beans and tomatoes, mixing well. Add pasta and heat through. Serve with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: aunt joyce's icebox pie
directions: Bottom Layer:
Sift flour; mix with margarine and pecans. Pour into oblong 9 x 12-inch pan and press together.
Bake in a 400° oven until almost brown.
Cool.

title: pecan fruit cookie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add dates, cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach mushroom salad
directions: Cut spinach into long thin pieces (like you cut cole slaw). Mix with cheese and mushrooms.
In separate bowl, mix together balsamic vinegar and olive oil.
Pour over salad and grind fresh pepper to taste.
Great when served with garlic bread!

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Spread into greased oblong pan. Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 25 minutes). Cut into pieces to serve.

title: jello fluff salad
directions: Add two cups of hot water to Jell-O.
While Jell-O is cooling, blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip to sugar and cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Add cooled Jell-O to mixture and refrigerate.

title: holiday dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and cottage cheese until creamy.
Add salt, garlic, mayonnaise and milk.

title: carrot cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add carrots and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured round cake pans (3).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost.

title: moon balls(uncooked)
directions: Blend well.
Chill.
Form into balls and roll in any type of cereal or crushed nuts.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In saucepan cook milk and salt until slightly heated.
Stir in rice.
When mixture reaches boiling point, lower heat and simmer about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add raisins and cook until rice is done, about 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup evaporated milk and cook a few minutes longer.
In mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and remaining milk.
Stir some of the rice mixture into the egg mixture.
Slowly add to mixture in saucepan and cook slowly until it thickens a bit, about 3 minutes.
Do not overcook as it will curdle.
Pour in bowl and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add chopped vegetables in a large bowl.
Mix Good Seasons as directed on package.
Mix together with vegetables.
Toss 1/2 jar of salad seasoning into bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: mince
directions: Brown hamburger in cooking pot.
Drain off fat.
Return hamburger to pot and add water and seasoning.
Bring to a boil. Add vegetables.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Lightly thicken with 1 1/2 tablespoons cornstarch (dissolved).

title: seven minute frosting #1
directions: Mix sugar, cream of tartar, salt, egg whites and water in a 2-quart mixing bowl.
Set over simmering water.
Beat with portable electric mixer about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove from water and continue beating a few minutes.
Beat in vanilla.
Spread between layers and on top and sides.
Sprinkle coconut on top of frosting between each layer and top of cake.

title: hawaiian sweet potato bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine mashed potatoes, milk, margarine, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix until well blended, using mixer set at medium speed.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, alternately layer potato mixture, pineapple and raisins, ending with potato mixture.
Pour sauce over potato dish. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper, celery and garlic in butter until melted. Add shrimp, soup, green onion and pimento and juice.
Heat until bubbling.
Add rice and mix well.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and put in a freezer overnight.
Take it out about 15 minutes before serving time. Chop with food chopper and add ginger ale.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Add the beaten eggs and vanilla and mix.
Add the baking soda, dissolved in 1 Tbsp. hot water.
Then add the flour sifted with the cream of tartar and salt.
Add the coconut and mix to a dough.
Shape into 2 long rolls and chill until firm.
Then slice and bake in a moderate oven for about 12 minutes.

title: yellow rice and chicken
directions: Cut chicken in quarters and fry in oil with
onion and garlic. When done, add tomatoes and water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add bay leaf, salt, rice, saffron and green pepper.
Stir thoroughly and place in moderately heated oven for 20 minutes.
Garnish with petits pois and pimentos.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3 cups boiling water.
Stir in 3 cups cold water.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly.
Peel and chop oranges; place in another bowl.
Add cranberries and sugar; stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Stir fruit mixture into thickened gelatin.
Pour into 12-cup mold or Bundt pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine by hand cake mix, almond extract, eggs, and pie mix. Bake in 9x13 greased and floured pan at 350° about 35 minutes. Icing: 1 cup sugar, 5 Tbsp. butter, 1/3 cup milk.
Bring mixture to boil and cook 1 munute. Remove froma heat and add 6 oz. of chocolate chips. Spread on cake while cake is still warm.

title: beef and cheese crescent pie(deep dish pizza)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom and sides of deep dish pan. Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper. Drain.
Add tomato sauce and salts.
Press rolls over bottom and sides of greased pan. Seal edges together.
Mix 1 cup grated cheese and egg. Spread over rolls. Top with meat mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup grated cheese over meat.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes for easier cutting. Cut in wedges.
Leftovers are delicious!

title: tangy broiled chicken
directions: In large, shallow, nonmetallic dish, combine vinaigrette and V-8 juice.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: salmon hash
directions: In a large bowl combine the potatoes, salmon, green pepper, green onions, dill, lemon rind, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon black pepper.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 450° for 6 minutes.
Let cool.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Combine all except vanilla and nuts in top of double boiler. Cook over rapidly boiling water, stirring frequently until thick, 10 minutes or more.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan (or oblong one), lined with waxed paper (or buttered).
Chill until firm (about 3 hours).
Cut into squares in about 1 1/2 hours or it will be a struggle trying to cut it.

title: spinach sandwich
directions: Squeeze water from spinach.
Place between paper towel and pat dry.
Mix with other ingredients except bread.
Add more sour cream, if necessary, for proper spreading consistency.
Trim crust from bread. Spread on mixture.
Top with bread slice. Cut into triangles.
Makes 56 sandwiches.

title: peanut play dough
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey.
Gradually add dry milk and cocoa, mixing with hands, until it reaches desired consistency. Store in airtight container.
Yields 2 pounds.
Preparation:
15 minutes.

title: old time cocoa bars
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Beat butter in large mixer bowl until light.
Gradually beat in sugar then vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in nuts. Spoon batter into pan and bake 25 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out barely clean.
Cool.

title: flaky crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together into a bowl; work in shortening with blender or 2 knives.
Add water to form dough, cutting and mixing all thoroughly while adding water.

Roll out on floured board, rolling only lengthwise and keeping the edges straight. Fold evenly into 3 layers (lengthwise as a sheet of paper would be folded to fit a business envelope); turn it half around and roll again.
