Repeat the folding and rolling twice.
Chill the pastry if possible before baking.
It is the folding and rolling that produces the flakiness.
Makes crust for 1 pie.

title: baked haddock with sour cream
directions: Arrange haddock on foil in a greased baking pan.
Mix sour cream, lemon juice, salt, maple syrup and corn flake crumbs and spread over the haddock.
Bake in moderately hot oven (425°) for about 35 minutes or bake in a small toaster oven to save power.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Soften tortillas in oil.
Brown flour in oil; add chili powder and water to make gravy.
Add salt and garlic powder to taste. Layer in large casserole:
tortillas, beef, cheese, onion and gravy.
Repeat.
Top with corn tortillas and gravy.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until bubbly throughout.
Can also roll mixture inside tortilla to make enchiladas.

title: pumpkin tart
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: plum cake
directions: Cut butter into flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, lemon peel and mace until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Mix egg and water. Stir into flour mixture.
Gather pastry into a ball, kneed just until smooth.
Press evenly on bottom and side of ungreased round layer pan, 9 x 1 1/2 inch.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter. Add flour and milk. Layer macaroni and Cheddar cheese in a greased casserole. Top with bread cubes and pour mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: nut brittle
directions: Spread nuts close together in buttered shallow pan. Heat sugar in heavy sauce pan until melted and a light golden color. Remove from heat, quickly stir in salt, soda and vanilla, Pour over nuts. When cold break into pieces.

title: quick and easy snack cake
directions: Blend cake mix, eggs, water and oil at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate bits over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Stir well.
Place mixture into muffin pan.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven until brown (approximately 15 minutes).
Makes 6 muffins.

title: punch lorraine
directions: Boil sugar in 6 cups of water for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add frozen orange juice, frozen lemonade and pineapple juice.
Smash bananas; add juice of lemon.
Freeze until mushy.
Add ginger ale.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender (about 20 minutes).
Melt oleo and stir in flour.
Add milk and seasonings.
Cook until thickened. Add cheese and stir until the cheese has melted and blended.
Cut the cabbage into bite-sized pieces and place in a buttered casserole.
Pour the sauce over the cabbage and blend well.
Cover with buttered breadcrumbs and bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: pork chops and corn
directions: Grease pan.
Place pork chops in a single layer.
Place pepper and onion over chops.
Pour corn over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Put seasonings in a cloth bag and bring to a hard boil with vinegar and sugar.
Put squash mixture in and boil 3 minutes.
Put in canning jars and seal properly.
Makes 4 pints.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour, then stir in juice.
Fold in pineapple and cheese.
Put in buttered dish.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Saute onion in 3/4 stick of margarine until they turn clear. Add soup and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Fold in sour cream. Pour over hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt remaining margarine and mix with crushed corn flakes.
Spread corn flake mixture on top of hash browns and bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: chicken pot pie casserole
directions: Cut up cooked meat.
Add Veg-all.
Add soup and put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° till bubbly.
Add unbaked biscuits to top and continue baking until biscuits are done - lightly browned on top.

title: pasta veggie salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Do not overcook.
Drain pasta and rinse with cold water.
Pour into large bowl.
Add broccoli, tomatoes, olives, cheese and dressing.
Toss well. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and shredded carrots over top.
Cover and refrigerate until served.
Great for picnics.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and celery in skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Add ground beef mixture.
Bake in a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered, then sprinkle with chow mein noodles and bake another 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Makes 8 servings.

title: poule a la marguerite
directions: Smear paste on skirt steaks (mixture will liquify as it marinates, at least 1 hour).
Must be barbecued for full flavor.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Mix. Form dough into rolls 1-inch to 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Chill or freeze.
Thin slice dough and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° approximately 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix honey, peanut butter and dry milk together.
Form into balls and roll in cereal or nuts.
Makes 50 balls.

title: brownies(never fail)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray (Pam) or grease a shiny* 9 x 11-inch cake pan; lightly flour, if desired.

title: white icing
directions: Beat with mixer until fluffy.

title: coleslaw for freezing
directions: Blend together with slaw and freeze.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven in a 5 x 9-inch greased loaf pan for 65 to 70 minutes or until the loaf sounds hollow when tapped with a table knife.

title: sun dried tomato spread
directions: Cook garlic in olive oil until brown; add wine and dried tomatoes. Cook about 10 minutes. Place cooked ingredients and remaining ingredients into a food processor and process until smooth. Serve with toasted baguette slices.

title: white mountain ice cream
directions: Separate eggs and make soft custard of the milk, egg yolks and sugar. Beat egg whites stiff and over them, pour the hot custard. Mix thoroughly. Add the vanilla and salt and when cold, the whipping cream and fresh fruit.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften
cream
cheese
with
mixer along with seasoning salt. Put
mixer away.
Mix other ingredients with fork.
Add this to cream
cheese mixture and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Make into a ball and roll in nuts.
Return to refrigerator until ready to use.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, oil, vanilla
and egg.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Add
flour, oats, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes or until
light
golden
brown.
Makes
dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly. Save a little of this mixture to sprinkle on pie before baking. Cook cornstarch, sugar, salt and milk in double boiler until mixture begins to thicken; add slightly beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Continue cooking until thick, stir constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Place peanut butter mixture in bottom of pie shell; add cream filling, then egg white with a little cream of tartar.
Place over filling.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
If yoy double the recipe, it will make 3 (9-inch) pies or 2 (9 3/4-inch) or deep dish.

title: candy covered pecans
directions: Cook sugar and Pet milk to soft ball stage.
Add flavoring and oleo.
Beat until cool.
Add pecans and mix to cover.
Spread on wax paper to dry.

title: no egg wonder cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until almost smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: homemade ranch dressing mix from scratch
directions: Place in storage container.
When ready to mix 1 pint, use 3 tablespoons mix to 1 cup buttermilk and 1 cup mayonnaise.
Can be used as marinade for fish, etc.
Also friends have told me to cut out some calories using yogurt for most of mayonnaise.

title: chocolate texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil 2 sticks margarine, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup water.
Cool.
Then pour over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, slightly beaten, buttermilk or sour cream and cinnamon.
Pour into a jelly roll pan 11 x 17 x 1-inch greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: turkey supper sandwich
directions: Place asparagus with its own liquid in pan.
Place turkey on top of asparagus.
Heat to serving temperature.
Melt butter in another pan, blend in flour and gradually stir in milk.
Cook on medium heat until thickened, stirring to keep smooth.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add mushrooms (drained), shredded beef, Worcestershire sauce and pepper to taste.
Toast bread.
Place turkey slice on each bread slice.
Cover with drained asparagus and spoon sauce over sandwiches.
Serves 5.

title: beef stew italiano
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat into flour and brown in cooking fat or oil in a large skillet.
Pour off drippings.
Sprinkle fennel seed over meat.
Add water and garlic. Cover tightly and cover slowly for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add onions and continue cooking, covered, for 15 minutes.
Stir in green pepper and continue cooking, covered, for 5 to 7 minutes. Add tomatoes, cooking another 5 minutes, or until heated through. Serve with macaroni.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Mix with soup, milk, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, sprinkle remaining onions on top and return to oven.

title: lemon pudding(from 1879 cookbook)
directions: Pour this mixture into rich crust of pastry.
After adding grated lemon rind, partially bake it.
Beat egg whites very stiff and add spoonful of sugar for each egg; then add lemon juice. Pour this meringue over the pudding and brown it quickly.

title: edible craft dough cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar.
Add egg yolks, soda, cream of tartar and vanilla, beating well. Gradually add flour, mixing well.
Divide dough into 4 equal portions.
Color one red, one yellow, one green and leave one plain.
Wrap each separately in plastic wrap; chill at least one hour.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy pan or slow cooker.
It's best to put spices in a tea strainer or tie in cheesecloth; otherwise cider will have to be strained before serving.
Cover and turn heat very low (below boiling temperature).
Let heat from two to eight hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender in boiling water; remove bones and skin.
Mix stuffing according to package directions and line bottom of casserole with half.
Cover with chicken.
Then mix sour cream with soup and pour over chicken.
Top with remaining 1/2 of stuffing.
Pour 1 cup broth over this and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Pare, core and cut apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Combine all other ingredients in order given and beat to make a smooth batter.
Pour half into a 9 or 10-inch angel cake pan.
Arrange half the apples over batter and cover with remaining batter.
Top with rest of apples, arranging evenly over batter.
Place in preheated 350° oven and bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake is golden brown.
Turn out of pan carefully and let stand on rack to cool.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix oil and vinegar.
Beat well with mixer, then add sugar, catsup, salt and pepper to taste.
Beat well.
Do not add onions until you're done.
Mix in by hand.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine meat and onion in large skillet.
Cook until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain well.
Return to skillet and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: In long cake pan, melt margarine.
Pour in fruit mixture of apples (or other fruit), 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup self-rising flour and cinnamon on top of melted butter.
Mix batter of 1 1/2 cups self-rising flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: venison lasagna
directions: Brown venison in oil.
Combine tomato sauce, basil, salt, sausage, onion, tomatoes, sugar, parsley and pepper and simmer 45 minutes.
While simmering, cook 8 ounces of noodles according to package directions; drain.
In a casserole dish, alternate in 2 layers:
noodles, venison, sauce, Cheddar or Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: veal cutlets a la libera
directions: Pound cutlets flat on both sides.
Beat together eggs, water, seasonings, parsley and cheese.
Dip cutlets into flour, then into egg mixture and finally into bread crumbs, coating well on both sides.
In a heavy skillet, saute garlic clove in 1-inch of oil until light brown; remove and discard garlic.
Over medium heat, fry cutlets in same oil until golden brown on both sides.
Serve hot, garnished with lemon wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: heavenly lemon supreme pie
directions: Combine in large bowl condensed milk and lemon juice; stir, then add 3/4 of Cool Whip, mixing well.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate pie.
Serve after it has been chilled.

title: country steak and gravy
directions: Wet bread crumbs with milk; crumble up in meat.
Mix and pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, cut in serving pieces and roll in flour.
Brown in oil quickly. Place in baking dish.
Cover with the 3 soups and water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
May add more water if needed.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Add pumpkin, baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan 50 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: homemade hominy
directions: Wash and pick out bad grains.
Add to 1 gallon water in black pot
with
heaping
teaspoon
Mary
War lye.
Stir to dissolve. Add corn to mixture.
Boil until outer skin of corn comes loose. Stir
until all the skin is off, staying with it and stirring constantly
as to not stay in lye bath too long. Remove
from fire
when
corn skins slip off between fingers. Drain
lye water off; pour more water into pot.
Drain again 2 or
times.
Now wash in pan or sink, washing several times, stirring
with
wooden spoon.
Keep
hands
out
(wear rubber gloves).
Now
with gloves off, run water over corn until you feel
no
slick
feeling to grains of corn.
Put corn into pot and
cook
to
6 hours, adding water as needed.
Do not put corn in aluminum.

title: christmas pudding candy
directions: Cook sugar, cream and butter to soft ball stage.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in fruit and nuts.
If coconut is coarse, grind it. When well mixed, roll as for meat loaf.
Wrap in dampened cloth, then in waxed paper and store to ripen.
Allow at least 2 weeks before using.
Slice into squares or grease hands and roll into balls.
Roll in nuts or coconut.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Cook to soft ball stage and test by dropping in cold water. If firm ball is formed, candy is ready.
Add a little vanilla and a pinch of salt.
Add a lot of nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.

title: robert redford dessert
directions: Combine flour, butter and nuts and press into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and half of the whipped topping; blend until smooth.
Spread over baked crust.
Beat together the two puddings and milk.
Whip until well blended. Pour into crust.
Spread remainder of whipped topping on top. Refrigerate.

title: aileen's christmas casserole
directions: Beat eggs well. Gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in other ingredients. Turn into 2-quart casserole (ungreased). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and stir with wooden spoon (while still hot).
Let cool.
Form into small balls. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Mix in strawberries and juice, pineapple and juice, bananas, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and freeze. Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.

title: berry baked chicken breasts
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy peanut butter balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine and confectioners sugar. Blend well.
Add cereal and blend into peanut butter mixture. Form in 3/4-inch balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Makes about 75 balls.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all of the above, refrigerate approximately four hours and eat!

title: my best recipe salad mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat syrup to a boil; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese, pineapple, pimento, celery and salt.
Blend well.
Fold into cooled gelatin.
Whip cream until stiff and fold into gelatin. Turn mixture into a mold and chill.
Unmold and serve on crisp greens.
(Makes 6 to 8 servings.)

title: cream cheese fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and pineapple.
Add fruit cocktail.
Add cut up cherries and marshmallows.

title: garlic chicken kabobs
directions: In a glass or stainless steel bowl, whisk together the lemon juice, oil, salt, pepper and oregano.
Add the onion, garlic and parsley, mixing well.
Cut the chicken into large cubes.
Toss in dressing.
Let stand for 8 to 10 hours in the refrigerator.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Steam vegetables in steamer or in microwave. Cook fettucine in chicken broth until tender; drain. Combine vegetables and pasta. Add basil to salad dressing; toss into pasta and vegetables. Sprinkle with Parmesan and parsley.

title: chicken burritos(makes 8 servings)
directions: In large, deep skillet, combine chicken, taco seasonings and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
In same skillet, heat oil.
Add rice; saute until golden.
Add remaining 2 1/2 cups of water, tomato sauce and lemon pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in chicken mixture, tomato and green onions; blend well.
Heat 5 minutes.
Place a heaping 1/2 cup filling on each tortilla.
Fold insides and roll to enclose filling.
Place filled burritos, seam side down, on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° for 5 minutes to melt.
May garnish with salsa or guacamole.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potatoes; boil until done.
Mash with fork; measure out 1 cup.
Mix with powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mixture will be runny. Add coconut; mix well.
Refrigerate until firm.
Make into logs; cover with chocolate.
Roll in nuts of your choice (pecans or walnuts, etc.).
Keep cool and slice as wanted.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of buttered casserole.
Add celery, onion and peppers.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on layers, then add tomatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: salsa dip
directions: Microwave cheese in microwave dish on High for 5 minutes or until melted. Add salsa and mix. Cook ground chuck and drain. Add chuck to cheese and mix. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet potatoes crunch
directions: Mix butter, sugar and coconut into mashed sweet potatoes while hot.
Place in casserole dish.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix eggs until frothy, then add sugar and flour.
Pour in melted butter; add milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into 8-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes until brown and firm.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: spinach-feta souffle(main dish for 2 to 3)
directions: Mix all items except eggs. Beat eggs until foamy and fold into cheese mixture. Put in souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oven baked brisket
directions: First Day:
Sprinkle garlic salt, celery salt and liquid smoke over brisket.
Marinate in Ziploc bag for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Cut bananas in chunks, add eggs and blend in blender. Pour over a box of yellow cake mix.
Blend well with mixer. Mix in nuts. Pour into 3 small or 2 regular size loaf pans. Bake at 350 for approximately 35 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, oats and flour together.
Place half of mixture in bottom of slightly oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place apples on top of mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar over apples; spread additional butter over sugar.
Spread other half of oat mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Bake in greased and lightly floured pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Blend together next 3 ingredients.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread on pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Can be frozen and eaten partially frozen.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Cook potatoes in enough water to cover.
Drain and mash.
Add butter, 1 egg and 1/4 cup bread crumbs; mix well.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Combine spinach, artichokes and chestnuts.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Melt cheese and butter together slowly.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
In drippings, cook onion until tender but not brown.
Combine other ingredients; add onion and crumbled bacon, mixing well.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot and bubbly all the way through, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: joe's pig picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 3 to 4 minutes at medium speed. Bake in 2 or 3 layers in a pre-heated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple drink
directions: Combine yogurt and orange juice in container of electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Slowly add enough ice cubes to bring mix to the 2-cup line.
Process until smooth and serve. Yields 2 cups (76 calories per 1/2-cup serving).
Contains 2.3 g protein, 0.5 g fat, 15.8 g carbohydrates, 0 mg cholesterol, 37 mg sodium and 75 mg calcium.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine roast and drained vegetables in a large, deep pan. Pour stewed tomatoes, including juice, over roast, then sprinkle minced onions, tapioca pudding and brown sugar over the roast. Oven bake for 6 to 12 hours at 250° in a conventional oven or a crock-pot.

title: shells(serves 6 to 7)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Boil shells until tender.
In large pan, add kidney beans, tomatoes, seasoning, sauce and sugar.
Heat to a boil.
Drain fat off ground beef; add to other ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve and eat.

title: executive potatoes
directions: Combine sour cream, soup, margarine, green onions and 1/2 of cheese.
Heat in saucepan.
Peel and grate potatoes and pour 1/2 of the mixture over them.
Layer another half of the potatoes over mixture and pour over rest of cream mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour and spread remaining cheese.
Bake another 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked blue fish
directions: Place each fish fillet on a piece of aluminum foil.
Cover each one with 3 strips of bacon, 3 slices of lemon and enough onion to cover generously.
Wrap the fillets tightly in the foil.
Cook at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Open the foil and brown slightly. Bacon will reduce the "gamey" taste of the fish.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: In 8 x 8-inch pan, sift together sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Stir in milk, vanilla and margarine.
Spread evenly in pan.
Mix together white and brown sugar and cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour 1 1/2 cups water over all and do not mix!
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top springs back.
Open box of ice cream and cut into 1-inch rectangular slices.
Each serving equals slice of ice cream topped with the cake and the hot fudge sauce (underneath).
Top with whipped cream and a cherry. Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook 4 servings of rice while fixing recipe.
Heat oil in skillet and add chicken and garlic; cook until chicken is brown on all sides.
Stir in onion, pepper, carrots, pineapple and juice, soy sauce, honey and vinegar.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger with taco seasoning.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Add mixture to hamburger.
Pour large bottle of Catalina French dressing over mixture.

title: party punch
directions: First boil sugar and water until clear and syrupy.
Mix all together and chill.
Just before serving, add 2 quarts ginger ale and 1 gallon of water.
Frozen strawberries may be added or frozen sherbet.

title: hot spiced wine mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Place mix in an airtight container and give with the recipe for Mulled Wine. Yields about 3/4 cup of mix.

title: strawberry and pineapple slush
directions: Boil the water and 1 cup sugar for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Blend the strawberries, pineapple, bananas, lemonade and orange juice in a blender.
Mix with the water and sugar mixture.
Pour into an ice cream pail and freeze overnight.
Take out of freezer 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Put in a punch bowl.
Pour 7-Up over the slush and serve.
Refreshingly different.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into a 9-inch (deep dish) unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over top of pie.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: mississippi fudge cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in bowl.
Melt oleo and add to sugar and cocoa.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Spread in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.
While hot, spread with marshmallow cream.
When cool, spread with frosting.

title: microwave-string bean casserole
directions: Put
beans
in	casserole.
Pour soup to which milk has been added
over
beans.
Add
bread
crumbs on top and cover. Put in microwave for 10 minutes at High temperature.

title: cocoa-coconut supreme pralines
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa into a thick walled pot.
Add butter, milk, corn syrup and salt.
Cook until melted.
Add coconut and cook over medium to low heat approximately 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and coconut extracts.
Stir and cool slightly.
Spoon onto waxed paper laid over paper towels with small ice cream scoop.
Makes 28 to 30 pralines.

title: swordfish steaks with dill-mustard sauce
directions: In large skillet, heat Italian dressing and cook fish over medium heat, turning once, 8 minutes or until fish flakes.
Remove to serving platter and keep warm.
Into skillet, add wine, then pepper, dill and mustard.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally, 8 minutes.
Stir in cream and heat 1 minute or until thickened.
Serve over fish.
Garnish, if desired, with baby vegetables.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; slice onions. Boil potatoes and onions for approximately 30 minutes; drain off liquid. Mash to coarse mixture; heat on very low heat. Add soup, milk and half and half. Add salt and pepper; add margarine; grate Cheddar cheese on top when served.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, oleo, syrup and salt in a saucepan; boil 5 minutes on medium heat.
Stir in vanilla and soda; mix well. Slowly pour over popcorn, stirring well to coat.
Heap onto cookie sheet.
Bake one hour in a 250° oven; do not stir.
Store in covered jar.
Don't break up, tends to break up by itself.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and brown in hot shortening in skillet. Remove chicken from skillet and place in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Saute onion, celery, green pepper, and garlic in butter. Sprinkle over chicken. Combine remaining ingredients except rice in saucepan and simmer over low heat for 10 to 12 minutes. Pour over chicken. Bake uncovered at 350° for one hour. Serve over rice. This is great to prepare a day ahead.

title: mexican hot cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix according to directions.
Mix all other ingredients into mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: spareribs country style
directions: In a large skillet, melt shortening.
Brown ribs on both sides in hot fat.
Add boiling water to almost cover meat; simmer, covered, until tender, or about 1 1/2 hours.
Potatoes may be cooked in the liquid, or a gravy may be made by thickening with flour and seasoning, after meat has been moved to serving platter. Spareribs go well with sauerkraut, too.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Simmer chicken and water with celery, parsley, onion and bay leaf for 1 hour on low heat. Drain chicken broth.
Remove chicken from bone and cut up into bite- sized pieces. Combine broth, chicken and rice and carrots in a saucepan. Cook for 30 to 40 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: dandelion greens
directions: Rinse greens through several waters and remove all discolored and broken leaves.
Place in a large saucepan and cover with salted water and salt pork.
Boil for 2 hours.
Drain off water and pat dry on paper towels.
Serve with bacon dressing.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage and peppers; store separately.
Mix Ramen noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds; store separately.
Mix dressing ingredients and store separately.
Mix all ingredients together right before serving.

title: baked breakfast
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, break off stems.
Mix together in a bowl the remaining ingredients.
Stuff mushrooms caps with the mixture. Drizzle over them lightly.
Bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Stir in Rice Chex until coated.
Put in paper sack with 2 1/2 cups powdered sugar.
Shake well.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In skillet melt butter; add mushrooms, parsley and onions. Cook until tender.
Add rice, pecans and ginger, stirring to mix. Add chicken broth; cook and stir until liquid is absorbed.
Wash and clean peppers. Cut off tops and carefully scoop out interior. Blanch peppers in boiling salted water 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from water and cool under running water.
Turn upside down to drain.
Spoon stuffing into peppers and replace tops. Arrange them in a baking dish and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: condensed milk
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in blender and process until smooth.
(To
make	it
richer,
add an additional 1/2 cup dry milk and 1/3 cup sugar.) Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Will keep at least 2 weeks.

title: holland health soup
directions: Wash barley and soak overnight in 6 cups of water.
Boil slowly for one hour.
Wash raisins and boil slowly until raisins are tender (about 1/2 hour).
Put in grape juice and serve.

title: marvelous chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Frost, if desired, or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing skin and bones.
Combine salmon, softened cream cheese, lemon juice, onion and horseradish in large bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Cover and chill overnight. Shape into a ball the next day.
Combine nuts and parsley.
Roll salmon ball in nut mixture, coating well.
Chill 2 or 3 hours. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mom's batter pizzelle
directions: Must use pizzelle maker to cook.
Yield: 7 dozen.

title: becon hill cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water or in microwave oven. Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar. Fold in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 9 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Carefully remove, using a flat spatula.

title: delma's meat loaf
directions: Mix all together; shape into a loaf and bake at 350° until done. For 50 servings, make 8 of the above recipe. You may wish to add a little catsup or meat loaf fixings to the top of meat loaf the last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, thoroughly.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread cheese evenly over it.
Pour the remainder of mixture over the cheese and bake in preheated oven at 375° for forty-five minutes or until it pulls away from side of pan.

title: hidden valley ranch buttered popcorn
directions: Mix first two ingredients. Toss with popcorn and serve immediately.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp, eggs, flour, sugar, spices, salt and baking powder; stir in milk last.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: hardy's texas chili(servings:  8)
directions: Sear meat; add other items and cover with water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cool; skim off grease.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of masa harina over chili; stir and bring to a boil.
Flavor better after letting set overnight.
Serve with sweet sliced pickles, Cheddar cheese, raw sliced onion, crackers and Kleenex.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place chips in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken next.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat until melted.
Pour over chicken. Pour 1 cup of chicken broth over the top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain all grease.
Add taco mix, salsa and cheese cut into small chunks.
Heat until cheese is melted stirring frequently so not to burn cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: fresh corn fritters
directions: Mix the corn kernels, corn muffin mix, egg and milk together. Drop by tablespoons in deep hot grease (365°). Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown; turn once. Drain well. Serve warm.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add raisins.
Mix in melted margarine, beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Mix in caraway seed if used.
Bake in greased bread pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Reduce to 325° and bake 10 minutes, or until pick comes out dry.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: monkey bread
directions: Line
Bundt pan with pecans.
Cut each biscuit in four; mix white sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit pieces into this. Place each
biscuit
over
pecans.
Mix melted oleo and brown sugar; pour
over	biscuits.
Bake
at
for 40 minutes. Remove from Bundt pan.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Chill soda pop.
When ready to serve, add soda pop to sherbet. Stir until mixture.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat white cake mix according to directions. Spread in a jelly roll pan which has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: cheese cakes
directions: Mix all
together with mixer.
Grease pans and fill 3/4 full. Bake
minutes
at
Do not burn!	May bake in petit four muffin tins.

title: coastal casserole delight
directions: Brown almonds and vegetables in margarine.
Mix with remaining ingredients (except cracker crumbs).
Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream until well blended. Serve with fresh fruit or cookies.

title: italian beef
directions: Bake roast at 325°, about 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, until medium well done.
Cool.
Slice very thin.
In large pan simmer remaining ingredients.
Add beef slices and simmer 1 hour or until done. Serve on hard rolls.
Spoon juice over meat on rolls.

title: quick zucchini quiche
directions: Mix together with fork.
Pour into a 10-inch greased pie plate. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed, simmering 15 minutes.
Remove from skillet and set aside; keep warm.
In same skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Add green onions, garlic, and ginger; cook 1 minute. Add shrimp; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly until pink.
Add chestnuts and prepared rice.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add pea pods and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Cook pudding and Jell-O with 4 1/2 cups water.
Boil 10 minutes.
Cool overnight.
Next day, add oranges and Cool Whip.

title: fruit salad #1
directions: Mix together and top with cherries.

title: grilled tenderloins
directions: Place tenderloins in a bowl.
Pour dressing over.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Grill over hot coals for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Slice and serve immediately. Yields 6 servings.

title: orange angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks until creamy. Gradually add sugar, then orange juice, flour and baking powder. Bake in angel food pan.
Start in cold oven and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: debbie's chinese salad
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Stir in soup base from Ramen noodles. Break noodles into small pieces.
To the melted oleo add noodles, croutons and nuts and cook over medium heat until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: stuffed pistolette rolls
directions: Brown meat and seasoning.
Add soups and broccoli.
Bake pistolette rolls until just brown.
Pull out inside of roll and make a cavity.
Add stuffing mix into cavity of roll and bake until brown.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Put ingredients in layers until done, in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put in refrigerator until chilled, then eat with tortilla chips.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into large greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter or oleo.
Blend flour, salt and vanilla into mixture and beat well.
Add eggs, then stir milk into mixture.
Line 2 (9-inch) pie pans with crust, pour in filling and bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for another 30 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in flour and nuts.
Makes a paste dough. Mash out in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 large container Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Mix sugar and cream cheese well.
Then add Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Let set in refrigerator while making rest of mix.
Add milk to pudding; mix well.
Pour in on top of mix.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Put 1 large container of Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: puppy chow or trash
directions: Mix first three ingredients over low heat until melted and mixed well.
Pour over cereal and mix well until all cereal is well coated.
Shake cereal in brown paper bag (outside) to which you have added the confectioners sugar.

title: barbecue butter beans
directions: In a bowl, combine beans, brown sugar, ketchup and onion. Transfer to a greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corned beef and cheddar casserole
directions: Melt half of the cheese in soup and milk.
Add the corned beef. Add cooked noodles, onion and sage. Cover with rest of cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes until bubbly and light brown.

title: fat-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on greased (Pam) cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan and line bottom with nuts and coconut. Prepare cake mix according to directions on box. Pour cake batter over nuts. Combine the margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar; spoon over the batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. The cream cheese frosting sinks to bottom to make icing with nuts in it. (May need to bake longer.)

title: hamburger hot beef
directions: Press raw meat into bottom of 3-quart dish.
Salt and pepper meat.
Pour English peas on top with liquid.
Cover with soup and arrange as many Tater Tots on top as possible.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: sweet-sour glazed ham
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil; set aside.
Slice away skin from ham.
Score (slice) fat on ham in a crisscross pattern.
Stud with whole cloves.
Place ham, fat side up, on rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until meat thermometer reads 140°.
Baste every 15 to 20 minutes with sauce.
Heat remaining sauce; serve with ham.
Makes 10 to 14 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the soda, vanilla and water; set aside.
Mix sugar, water and corn syrup.
Boil over medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 240°.
Stir in peanuts and margarine; stir until 300°. Remove from heat and add soda mixture.
Pour into two buttered pans (9 x 13-inch).
(Keep warm in 200° oven.)
When cool, break into pieces.

title: quick cookies
directions: Add eggs and cooking oil
to
cake mix; stir until well mixed. Allow approximately
teaspoonful
for
each cookie. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8	to
10	minutes.
Raisins,
chopped
nuts, coconut, chocolate chips, etc. may be added.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Soak beans overnight in 3 cups of water.
Drain beans and place in a large saucepan.
Add 3 cups of fresh water and cook, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Drain, rinse and set aside.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add onions and tomatoes; stir.
Put evenly on bottom of dish, then pour soup.
Top with Tater Tots. Bake in oven at 400° for approximately 1 hour.

title: easy louisiana yam and pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix egg, milk, cake mix and flavoring. Fold in yams and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grandmother's cookies
directions: Roll and cut out desired shapes.
Bake at 350°.

title: favorite icing
directions: Boil water and granulated sugar for a few minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, salt and egg.
Blend into syrup.
Add Crisco and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Yields enough for two 9-inch cakes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, butter and soup.
Add potatoes and 1/2 of Cheddar cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle last of cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake until top is brown.
Mix.
Will thicken as it sits.

title: christmas 24 hour salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan; gradually add half and half and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool. Combine pineapple and next 4 ingredients in large bowl; fold in egg mixture and whipping cream.
Cover and chill 8 hours; serve in lettuce lined bowl and garnish with grape clusters.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin loaves
directions: Beat eggs one at a time, add sugar, pumpkin, salt, cinnamon and oil and mix together.
Gradually add dry ingredients to the egg mixture.
Add in the chocolate chips and chopped walnuts. Pour into the 3 loaf tins and bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: candy corn(snack)
directions: Pop the corn and place in a large cake pan. Boil together sugar, Karo and margarine for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla, salt and soda.
Pour over popped corn and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: leche plan
directions: Scald the Carnation evaporated milk in double boiler 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks.
Add the sugar, milk and flavoring. Pour into 1-quart mold.
Place this in large pan half filled with water.
Steam or bake for about 1 hour or until mixture becomes firm.
Cool before removing from mold. (If desired, line mold with the caramel syrup before pouring in mixture for steaming or baking.)

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix well all ingredients and drop into fat by tablespoon. Brown, turn and serve warm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients, except carrots, bell pepper and onion. Heat to boiling point.
Add sliced bell pepper and onion; cook over medium heat about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add carrots and heat through.

title: caramel-mellow sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Heat, covered, on Full power for 2 1/2 to 4 minutes or until melted.
Stir several times during heating time.
Stir until smooth.
Serve over ice cream.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, cut into chunks or slices and place eggplant in water to cover.
Bring to a boil and when done, drain and mash; set aside. Melt margarine, add flour and stir.
When smooth, add milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Add eggplant to creamed mixture along with cheese, cracker crumbs, seasonings and beaten egg yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Turn mixture into a greased pan or dish and bake at 375° until firm, about 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pistachio pudding fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix in fruit and a handful of miniature marshmallows.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together in a large bowl:
flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and walnuts.
Beat together egg, bananas, milk and melted shortening.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir only until all ingredients are moist.
Pour in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: rabbit with dumplings
directions: Salt and pepper rabbit; cover with flour.
Put in heavy skillet in the cooking oil.
Sear on both sides.
Place in stew pot.
Cover with hot water.
Add thyme and bay leaves.
Cook until tender.
Now add dumplings to stew pot.
Cook until done.

title: crazy crunch
directions: In a large bowl, mix popped corn and nuts. Combine sugar, butter and syrup in heavy pan. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Stir constantly. Continue boiling for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until mixture turns a light caramel color and spins a thread. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Pour over popped corn and nuts. Spread on waxed paper to dry. Break into pieces and store in a tightly covered container.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt chips in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts and noodles (immediately) until evenly coated.
Drop on wax paper or cookie sheet to cool.

title: banana-caramel cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup milk, then mix with the cake mix, oil, eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring and butter flavoring.
Bake at 350°.

title: minty fudge brownies
directions: Mix and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 33 to 35 minutes at 350°. Cool completely.

title: how to cook greens(mustard, collards and turnips with roots)
directions: Heat on medium-low.
Custard mustard into the boiler on top of the oil.
Start with low heat.
Add seasoning; cover and cook slowly for 30 to 45 minutes.
I don't add any water, they will make enough liquid.
Stir them occasionally.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop pepper and onions.
Pour boiling water over pepper and onions; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain off water.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar; cook for 5 minutes.
Pack in can and seal.

title: **cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries through coarsest part of food chopper and pour sugar over them.
Soak gelatin in 1/3 cup of cold water then dissolve in 2/3 cup of hot water.
Add cranberries, marshmallows, pecans and orange juice.
Add pineapple but save juice for dressing.
Stir mixture and then place in refrigerator to congeal. If preferred, this dressing is used with the salad.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add pumpkin and vanilla. Add rest of ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fire proofing
directions: Boil water.
Dissolve Borax and boric acid.
Rinse your clothing, sheets, etc. in it.

title: rocky comfort chowder
directions: Bring water to boil; add salt and vegetables in order.
boil until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sugar, pepper and hot milk; mix.
Add butter and serve.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake in greased and floured pie pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot, topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and cool.
Cut onions and green pepper and mix with carrots.
Mix soup, sugar, salt, pepper, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, oil and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water; drain noodles.
Add corned beef and all other ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large mixer bowl beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and morsels.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes for chewier cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crispy cookies. Yields 4 dozen.

title: chili and spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Brown onion and green pepper in little oil. Mix tomatoes and spaghetti; add to mixture.
Mix well and put in large skillet or casserole.
Top with grated Cheddar.
Cover with heated chili.
Put on lid.
Put in slow oven and cook 30 minutes or longer if convenient.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine garlic
and anchovies.
Squeeze lemon on anchovies. Add Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and mustard and mix thoroughly. Add egg.
Whisk briskly to a creamy texture.
Add balsamic vinegar and olive oil.
Mix again thoroughly so as to preserve the texture.
Pour on the greens and mix lightly.
Add cheese; toss the greens.
Add croutons; toss again.
Add fresh ground pepper.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix and pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.
May be frozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the butter and sugar. Mix together the 3 dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, buttermilk and 2 eggs.
Rotate, adding dry ingredients and bananas to creamed mixture, stirring well after each addition.
Add nuts last.
Grease and flour pan.
Cook 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lobster stew
directions: Saute 3 to 4 minutes lobster meat in butter.
Add slowly milk and onion juice.
Do not allow to boil.
Season to taste and serve.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: california salad
directions: Cook until tender 2 pounds sliced carrots

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle one box of yellow cake mix (or butter cake mix) on top. Drizzle melted oleo over top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Before the last 15 minutes of baking time is over, add chopped pecans to top and finish cooking. Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Skin and cut chicken breasts in 6 to 8 pieces.
Marinate in buttermilk overnight.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, salt and pepper. Let stand 1 hour.
Roll in flour to coat.
Deep fry for 12 minutes.

title: chicken linguine
directions: Saute mushrooms in sherry and 1 tablespoon margarine in nonstick skillet 5 minutes.
Place chicken in saucepan; add water to cover.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Drain, let cool and shred.
Coat a saucepan with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion.
Saute until tender.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup broth.

Add 2 1/2 cups broth and flour mixture to onion; cook over medium heat until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in sour cream. Cook linguine according to directions on package omitting salt and fat; drain.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Turn pan until melted margarine coats the entire bottom surface. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over the melted margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over the crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
Refrigerate if desired. Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: greek-style salad
directions: Cut tomato wedges in half crosswise.
Combine them with salad greens,
onion
rings,
cucumber
and olives in a large bowl.

title: hot and sour spinach salad
directions: Combine bread crumbs and salt; stir well.
Dip cheese in egg whites; dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place cheese on a baking sheet lined with wax paper.
Freeze 30 minutes.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: Spread can of chili into casserole dish; spread cubed Velveeta into chili.
Microwave for approximately 5 to 7 minutes, mixing well or bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes, mixing well. Serve hot with nacho chips on the side.

title: praline grahams
directions: Place graham crackers side by side on a 15 x 10-inch greased cookie sheet with raised sides.
Boil oleo and sugar together for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Spread over crackers.

title: sauerberry meatballs
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Roll in 1-inch balls. Brown lightly; place in baking pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients for sauce.
Heat in saucepan until warm; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
May also be cooked in crock-pot.

title: rose spray
directions: Mix all together.
Put in spray bottle.
Use as a rose spray to combat bugs and diseases.
(Will work on other flowers as well.)

title: sausage bread
directions: Let bread rise as directed on package. Brown meat and vegetables together. After bread rises, roll out flat and place on a cookie sheet, one for each roll. Spread 1/2 the mixture in center of each loaf and top with 1/2 of each cheese. Fold bread over and tuck in ends. Brush with egg and bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together and press cake mix, egg and margarine into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over cake. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
As cake cools, it will fall.

title: orange slice squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to eggs.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients over candy until coated.
Combine mixtures and stir until well mixed.
Pour into greased 11 x 15-inch shallow pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add cold water and set aside. Whip together cream cheese, Cool Whip, 1 cup sugar and vanilla. Add jello mixture and whip again. Mix cracker crumbs, melted oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar and spread in cake pan, saving a little for the top. Pour in filling and chill.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring just to moisten (do not beat).
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Spoon into 3 floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done with toothpick test.
Cook in pan for 10 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine apples, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened; spread onto apples.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in large saucepan.
Add butter, salt, vanilla and milk; cook on medium heat until right consistency.
If gravy gets too thick, add more milk.
This is delicious over warm biscuits.

title: glazed apple rings
directions: Wash apple, but do not peel.
Core; cut apples in 1/2-inch slices.
In a medium bowl, toss apples with lemon juice.
In 10-inch skillet, combine sugar, corn syrup and 3/4 cup of water. Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes.
Layer apple slices in skillet.
Add remaining lemon juice in bowl.
Cook over medium heat, uncovered, and turn several times for 5 minutes or until glazed and tender. Serves 6.

title: poppy seed lemon bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms of four 5 1/2x3 inch mini loaf pans.
Combine ingredients in mixer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into pans.

title: broccoli casserole 2
directions: Mix together.
Cover.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Stir in 1/2 hour.
Use a 9 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.

title: yankee doodle casserole
directions: Saute in large skillet, first 5 ingredients.
Add salt and brown.
Add soup, noodles and 1/2 cup cheese to mixture.
Save 1/4 cup cheese for topping.
Bake 30 minutes in a greased casserole (crushed potato chips may be added on top).

title: cowboy potato casserole
directions: Layer all vegetable and cover with oleo.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350.
Place American cheese on top when baked.
Place in oven until cheese is melted.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press in bottom and sides of pan. Mix next ingredients and pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon pieces with onion until bacon is almost crisp.
Add green pepper, potatoes and water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer for 15-20 minutes, or until potatoes are fork tender.
Add half-n-half, clams with juices, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Bring back to heated temperature preference.
Do not boil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Fry bacon until very crisp.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain off grease.
Mix beans together.
Add ground beef. Crumble bacon and add it to beans with remaining ingredients. Bake about an hour or cook on stove top or in crock-pot.

title: curried zucchini soup(serves 5 to 6)
directions: Melt butter in frypan; add zucchini, garlic and scallions; cook, covered, over low heat until zucchini has softened but is not limp.
Transfer mixture to blender.
Add broth and cream and blend.
Add salt, pepper and curry powder to taste.
Serve hot or cold.
Nice first course.

title: focaccia
directions: In a 1-cup measure, combine yeast, 1/4 cup water and the sugar.
Stir. Let stand 5 minutes.
Transfer to a bowl with remaining 1 1/4 cups of water, 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt and 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add 2 cups of flour and stir until smooth. Gradually add 1 more cup of flour and herbs, stirring until well combined.
On floured surface, knead dough until smooth and elastic, at least 10 minutes, adding remaining 1 cup of flour as needed.
(Dough will be soft.) Place in oiled bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Use heavy-duty mixer. When soft dough is formed, refrigerate overnight.
Cut in 8 equal portions.
Makes 8 (4 ounce) eggs.

title: cheesecake #4
directions: Beat the cream cheese and eggs until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition, then add the sugar, beating until smooth.
Mix in sour cream, lemon and vanilla.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes,
or until only a 3-inch circle in center shakes if pan is jiggled.
Serve at room temperature.
If made a day in advance, refrigerate.
Top with Sour Cream Topping.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Put Carnation, sugar and chocolate in saucepan.
Set saucepan on burner and turn heat to low.
When sauce starts to boil, cook for 15 minutes.
Stir every 2 to 3 minutes.
After 15 minutes, take sauce from stove and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Great on ice cream.

title: cheesy quick chicken
directions: In plastic bag, mix together dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in melted butter.
Drop into dry mixture.
Shake to coat.
Place in foil-lined pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is golden and fork-tender.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Put rice in bottom of pan and lay chicken parts on top.
Mix sherry, mushroom soup and celery soup.
Pour over rice and chicken.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on top and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: hot chili con cheese dip
directions: Cut
cheese
into
pieces
and	melt
in
top of double boiler or over very low
heat
in a heavy pan. Chop onions and peppers very fine and
add to cheese sauce.
Add salt, oregano and A.1. sauce. Cool mixture until onions are tender. Gradually add milk or cream. Keep hot. Serve with chips.

title: country meat loaf
directions: In a skillet cook celery, onion and garlic until tender.
Set aside 1/3 cup chili.
In a large bowl combine remaining chili, ground beef, ground turkey, egg, bread crumbs, pepper sauce, salt, thyme, cumin and cooked celery mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°. Place in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine yogurt, milk, sugar, oil and egg.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Fold in berries.
Combine the two mixtures.
Stir only until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into well-greased or paper lined muffin cups.
Top with crumb topping (see below). Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges. Mix together Cool Whip and milk. Add lemon juice. Fold in pineapple and oranges. Add pecans. Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening; add vanilla and eggs which have been well beaten.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar and add to other ingredients.
Form into roll and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and place on unbaked cookie sheet; bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: vegetable chicken pot pie
directions: In a large skillet, melt oleo.
Add celery and stir over low heat until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, onion powder, thyme and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in vegetables and chicken and heat through.
Spoon into a 12 x 9-inch dish.
Put biscuits along the side or on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and biscuits are done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine brown sugar, peanut butter, shortening, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in egg just until blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until just beginning to brown and set.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to foil. Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and serve cold.

title: brigadeiros(brazilian candy)
directions: Mix ingredients together over a low heat, stir until mixture thickens and leaves the bottom of pan.
Cool slightly, roll into small balls; then roll in any type of confetti.
You can put them into individual candy paper cups.
If overcooked, it crumbles; if undercooked, it becomes sticky.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add onion, celery, peppers and spices. Saute for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, wine and water and simmer for 1 hour.
Cool down.
(Best when made a day ahead.)

title: doris' clam chowder (cape cod)
directions: Melt margarine in deep sauce pan.
Add onion and cook slowly until golden brown.
Add baby clams in liquid and potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat.
Slowly add milk and whipping cream.	Mix corn starch in a little cold milk and add to mixture to thicken.
Return to heat. Do not boil.
Serve immediately.
Serves 3 - 4.

title: potatoes anna
directions: Peel potatoes, if desired, and slice into 1/8-inch slices. Arrange potato slices in 2 circles with the pieces overlapping in a lightly greased pie pan.
Melt butter or margarine with salt and drip evenly over potatoes.
Cover dish with foil and bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and continue to bake until potatoes are tender and crispy (about 35 to 40 more minute). Serves 4 to 5.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain and cool.
Combine celery, onion and pimientos.
Blend in Miracle Whip salad dressing, French dressing, salt and pepper.
Slice 2 hard-cooked eggs and fold into salad.
Garnish with 2 sliced hard-cooked eggs, paprika and parsley.
Serves 12.

title: cheese spread for ritz crackers(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Allow flavors to blend about an hour. Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: apples and bacon
directions: Peel and thinly slice the apples.
Place apples in a large frying pan with a small amount of water (1/2 cup).
Cook until softened, but not pulped.
Cook bacon and cut into small pieces. Add bacon and brown sugar.
Cook together until sugar is totally melted.
Serve with whole wheat toast.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil unpared potatoes until tender.
Drain and peel.
Shred coarsely.
Place in 2 or 3-quart casserole.
Pour melted butter over potatoes.
Mix together soup, sour cream, milk, onion and cheese.
Pour evenly over potatoes.
Do not mix.
Cover the top with buttered crumbs mixed with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Combine the listed ingredients.
Pour in a greased baking dish.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add shrimp, consomme, rice, salt and pepper to taste. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook as any other rice dish.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Melt butter, add seasonings.
Pour over chicken arranged in single layer.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, vanilla and cream cheese. Add 2 eggs and beat until fluffy. Add flour and remaining eggs alternately, beating well after each addition. Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan. (I spray my pan with Pam instead and it does a good job.) Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Test with a cake tester or toothpick. Cool and remove from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese. Place mixture in a large, oiled casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak crumbs in milk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Mold into a flat loaf about 1 to 2 inches thick. Spread with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May spread mashed potatoes on top. Garnish with sliced tomatoes and mushrooms. Return to oven or broiler until tomatoes are cooked and potatoes are slightly browned.
Yield: 6 generous servings.

title: nol's etouffee
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, prepare roux by cooking the flour in the microwave for 2 minutes.

Stir and continue to microwave in 1 minute increments stopping to stir frequently to prevent roux from burning or getting hot spots, continuing this process until the flour turns dark tan. If you burn and get hard black pieces, you can remove with spoon and the rest of the roux will be okay.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Mix the soup, sour cream, cheese and onion together, then pour into hash browns and mix well.
Bake in casserole dish for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken extra
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice, using chicken stock as liquid.
Mix soup with mayonnaise.
Combine all other ingredients in separate bowl, add soup mixture and mix well.
Place in large, greased casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbles.
Top with cheese if desired.
Serves 14 to 16 and can be frozen before cooked.

title: cheese balls
directions: With fingers, mix cheese, flour, butter and enough water to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough into small balls, about 3/4 inch diameter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Layer in 2-quart casserole as listed.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir to satin finish.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugars and butter until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour. Serve warm... with ice cream is good.

title: german potato salad
directions: Pour above mixture over potato mixture while hot.
Serve.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cover bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with marshmallows. Prepare cake mix according to directions on box; pour over marshmallows.
Crush strawberries and combine with dry gelatin mix.
Spoon strawberry mixture over batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: brazil nut fruit cake for brazil nut lovers
directions: Mix fruit together. Mix cake dough together and combine with fruit.
Pour into wax paper lined well greased pans and pack well.

title: clam chowder soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add all other ingredients and mix. Cook in crock-pot on high for 6 hours.

title: whole wheat rolls *
directions: Mix first four ingredients and let set until lukewarm.
Add yeast and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, one cup at a time, mixing well into liquid ingredients.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes. Punch down.

title: sour cream orange nut loaf
directions: Grate orange for cake batter.
Mix baking soda with sour cream in a large container, as it swells (almost doubles).
Beat together sugar and shortening until creamy, then eggs.
Add flour and sprinkle of salt alternately with sour cream, then add walnuts and/or raisins, 1 teaspoon vanilla and orange peel.
Bake in loaf pan about 1 hour at 325°.
Remove from oven and immediately pour over the juice of the orange with 1/2 cup sugar.

title: springtime salad
directions: Stir dry pudding in with Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows, crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges. Refrigerate.

title: creamy smooth ice cream
directions: Pour 1 cup of milk and set to the side.
Heat remaining milk. Combine flour and eggs and mix with 1 cup of milk.
Stir into hot milk and continue stirring until it comes to a boil.
Cool, then add vanilla and condensed milk.
Freeze.

title: baked stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise.
Scoop inside out with a teaspoon. Set aside.
Boil shells for 3 minutes.
Fry onion, zucchini scoopings and drained mushrooms in butter or oleo.
Remove from oleo into a bowl.
Add egg and bread crumbs.
Mix. Sprinkle cheese over top and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Bake in a long Pyrex dish.

title: flacky flick salad
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add 1/2 of crushed cookies.
Place the rest of the cookies on top.
Better made a day ahead of serving.
Refrigerate.
Can be served as a dessert.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef and onion. Add soup, Worcestershire sauce and cheese. Simmer 30 minutes; stir to blend.

title: fresh vegetable herb dip
directions: Put all ingredients except milk into bowl and beat at low speed until smooth; gradually beat in milk.
Cover and chill for several hours to blend flavors.

title: deer jerky
directions: Slice raw meat into very thin slices.
Mix all ingredients. Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish with sauce mix.
Layer meat in sauce, brushing tops of each layer.
Pour remaining sauce on top.
Marinate for 48 hours.
Dry in 140° oven by placing meat strips on oven rack or cake rack for about 8 hours.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and egg.
Add dates; mix and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Make into small balls.
Roll in coconut and/or powdered sugar.
Very good!

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Fry hamburger with onions, celery and all of your favorite seasonings until done (drain).
Put back on stove, add tomato soup and green beans.
Do not add water to soup.
Stir in beans and top with biscuits of your choice.
Bake in oven until biscuits and cheese are melted and biscuits are brown.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Grease pan or spray.
Cook broccoli until done.
Put broccoli in pan.
Melt cheese on top of broccoli.
Mix crackers and oleo together and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Grease long casserole dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Cover with sliced cheese.
Mix soup and 1/4 cup water.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over soup.
Spoon melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, uncovered.

title: chinese chicken cornucopias
directions: Cut each wonton wrapper into circles using a large biscuit cutter (about 3 inch). Wrap the circles around metal cream horn forms, wetting the edges to seal.
Deep fry at 375 degrees.

When delicately browned, remove from oil and drain on absorbent paper. To remove the cones from the forms, use a clean dish towel, holding the larger end of each cone in one hand and give the cone a little twist with the other hand (using towel to prevent burns). These can be made a week in advance of when you plan to use them. Keep stored in a tightly sealed container or plastic zip-type bag. To prepare filling: combine the chicken and onions.
In a small bowl combine the mustard, sesame oil, and soy sauce.
Mix well. Pour over chicken and onions.
This is best if refrigerated overnight for flavors to
blend.
Before stuffing the cones with this mixture, stir in enough mayonnaise to bind the filling.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients in another bowl and mix well.
Add shortening and sugar; mix well. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 55 minutes. Cool before slicing.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients, except corn flakes or potato chips.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with the chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Reserving 1/2 cup of mixture, press remainder into 10 x 14-inch pan.

title: salami
directions: Mix seasonings and then mix into meat. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Form into 1 pound rolls.
Place on broiler pan and bake at 300° about 1/2 hour or until inserted thermometer measures 155°.
Serve with crackers.

title: savory cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water 7 minutes or until tender. Drain well.
Combine all other ingredients and mix with cabbage. Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients. In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and onion. Chill. Combine all ingredients just before serving.

title: parisian soup
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in 2 cups of water until tender.
Mix oleo and butter.
Add celery and onions.
Saute until onions are clear.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add bouillon and milk. Stir.
Add the vegetables, ham, pepper and Accent.
Salt to taste. Stir until thick and smooth.
Makes 3 quarts of soup.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: In small pan, melt oil and butter.
Stir in thyme.
Cut potatoes in half; place in small baking pan.
Pour oil mixture over potatoes; coat evenly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Roast at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 1.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with milk in top of double boiler.
(Do this before mixing cake as it will take a while to unwrap and melt caramels).
Combine cake mix with water, butter and eggs in large mixer bowl and blend on low speed 30 seconds, then beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour half the batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cake puffs up and is gooey.
Pour caramel-milk mixture over partially baked layer to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips evenly over caramel.
Pour remaining batter over all and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until top springs back when touched lightly. Cool in pan and cut into squares.
Top with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: fish and herbs
directions: Place fillets in greased baking dish.
In saucepan, melt margarine. Add soy sauce and herbs.
Pour over fish and bake at 375° allowing 10 minutes per inch thickness of fish.
When almost done, remove fish from oven and sprinkle with mushrooms and onions and arrange lemon slices on fish.
Make sure topping is well basted with pan juices. Return fish to oven and bake another 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily and topping is heated through.

title: sour cream chive biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Stir in sour cream and chives.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead lightly.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Combine oats, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut into butter.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake
at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot dip(makes 1 dozen pints)
directions: Chop
peppers,	onions,
garlic and tomatoes and put in large boiler.
Add
vinegar,
sugar
and salt.
Boil on medium heat until
mixture tastes done, for about 1 hour.
Stir often as mixture
settles to the bottom.
Pour 1/2 pint of water and cornstarch and shake well.	Add this to boiling mixture, using a small amount at a time until your mixture is thickened.
Add hot sauce
and	catsup.
Boil
about 30 minutes more, stirring often. Process 20 minutes in pint jars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Fry onions and celery in small amount of butter.
Add soup, broth and seasonings.
Add chicken and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour into quart casserole and top with noodles and nuts.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes.
Uncover for last 5 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: fiesta yellow squash
directions: In large skillet, melt butter; add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Add squash and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and cook over moderate heat for 10 minutes or until crisp tender.

title: hasty fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo and put fruit in baking dish.
Pour oleo over fruit. Mix
the
dough and pour over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: monster cookies(recipe can be halved)
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and stir. Form in hands or drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Delicious!!!

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand.
Beat eggs in oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: With a spoon, mix well the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; mix again with spoon.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 20 minutes.

title: swedish tarts
directions: Cream
