butter and cream cheese; add flour and mix well. Roll in
1/2-inch
roll.
Slice
in
30 slices.
Press in tart mold being
careful
not to leave any hanging over edge.
Bake 11 minutes at 425°.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Dot bottom of ungreased pan with oleo squares.
Mix flour, sugar,
milk and baking powder.
Pour over oleo in pan.
Spread fruit into pan, allowing batter to bubble through.
Bake at 350° for 35
minutes in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook
chicken	until
tender.	Cool.
Tear
apart
and remove bones.
Saute
onion
in margarine, adding soups, milk and chilies.
Mix well.
Drop tortillas in chicken broth 2 at a time. Soak for 2 minutes.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan using 6 tortillas (tear up), then put a layer of chicken, then half
of the
soup mixture, then a layer of soaked tortillas, then
a layer
of chicken, then the rest of the soup mixture. Put grated cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.

title: supreme beef casserole
directions: Lightly brown hamburger in skillet, drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce, salt, sugar and garlic.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Meanwhile, cook noodles and drain well.
Blend with fork, sour cream, cream cheese and onions.
In greased casserole, pour small amount of meat sauce; cover with layer of noodles and grated cheese.
Repeat layers, topping with meat sauce.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: bing cherry congealed salad
directions: Open cans of fruit and drain; save 1 1/2 cups of juice from fruit.
Dissolve Jell-O (both boxes) in 2 cups boiling water in large bowl.
Add the 1 1/2 cups of juice and let cool in refrigerator until it begins to set.
Add fruit and nuts and pour into large ring mold.
Return to refrigerator until firm.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet with sage, salt and pepper.
Add Italian seasoning just before meat is completely brown.
Meanwhile, cut onions and potatoes into thin slices.
In large casserole arrange a layer of potatoes, onions and meat.
Repeat until there are 6 layers in total.
Pour tomatoes on top and dot with margarine/butter.
Sprinkle paprika across top and bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: italian beef roll-up
directions: Mix together well beef, eggs, bread crumbs, milk, onion, oregano and garlic powder.
Pat meat into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle on foil or waxed paper.
Arrange salami slices atop meat, leaving a small margin on all sides.
Sprinkle grated cheese over salami. Starting from shortest end, roll up meat jellyroll fashion, lifting roll with foil.
Seal ends and edge by pressing meat together.
Sprinkle all surfaces of outside of roll evenly and generously with natural meat tenderizer.
Use no salt.
Place roll seam side down in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 55 to 60 minutes.
Top with cheese slices, overlapping; continue baking a few minutes just until cheese starts to melt.
Makes 8 servings.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour for a smooth, thick paste.
Let cool.
In medium bowl using electric mixer, beat sugar and shortening for 4 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup margarine/butter and beat for another 4 minutes.
Add salt, vanilla and cooked paste.
Beat for 4 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 1/2 x 2-inch round pans.
Mix together eggs, oil, sugar, food color and vinegar. Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda in a bowl.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to egg/sugar mixture.
Add almond and vanilla extract last.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until tests done.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Especially eggs and butter.
Cream butter, sugar and Crisco with electric mixer on medium until smooth and sugar has begun to dissolve.
Add eggs one at a time and mix until each yolk disappears.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Lower mixer speed to low to add flour alternating with milk, being careful not to overmix.
Add sour cream to mixture and vanilla.
Pour into pound cake pan and bake at 325° for 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted is clean.

title: vegetarian noodle dish
directions: Cook noodles with 2 teaspoons chicken seasoning and 1/4 teaspoon salt in 2 quarts water.
Then scramble eggs in large skillet with oil.
Cut eggs fine as they scramble.
Add vege chicken and garbanzo beans, mushroom soup and chicken seasoning. Cook a few minutes.
Add milk and butter.
Combine with noodles. Put in casserole and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl and let stand 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Beat eggs and stir into apple mixture.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: orange julius
directions: Place in blender; blend until ice is finely chopped.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up chicken.
Boil chicken until meat starts to separate from bones.
Remove chicken from water; strain off excess chicken fat from water.
Debone chicken.
Add bouillon cubes, salt, pepper and Season-All to original water.
Bring to a boil, making sure that all cubes are fully dissolved.
Add chicken to water mixture. Roll out biscuits in flour; cut into small dumplings.
Add dumplings to mixture.
After mixture has come back to a boil, reduce heat to medium.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring to keep dumplings rolling into mixture.
If desired, sweet peas can be added about 5 minutes before end of cooking time.
Yield: Makes enough to fill a lot of hungry bellies.

title: ambrosia pie(amazing)
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
In 12-inch skillet over medium
heat, in hot margarine/butter, cook apple slices until tender and crisp; about ten minutes, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.
Preheat oven
to
Line
pie pan with pastry.
In small bowl mix
flour,
cinnamon, salt and 2/3 cup sugar; toss with apple
slices.
Spoon filling into pie crust, mounding slightly.
Place top
crust
on filling.
Brush crust with some milk.
Sprinkle
pie
with one teaspoon sugar.
Bake pie 45 minutes or until golden.

title: carrot & raisin salad
directions: Toss raisins, carrots and pineapple together. Set aside. Stir together mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and sweetener. Add to carrot mixture. Refrigerate. Approximately 6 1/2 cup servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Put three kinds of cheese and Worcestershire sauce in blender and mix. Add half of the nuts and parsley.
Form in balls and roll in remaining nuts and parsley.
Put in a covered dish. Refrigerate and let stand at least three days before using.

title: congealed salad
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add to gelatin.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Measure 1 cup of the gelatin.
Fold into whipped topping.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill about 10 minutes.
Add fruit to remaining gelatin; gently spoon over creamy layer in pan.
Chill until firm (about 3 hours).
Cut into squares.
Garnish as desired.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine sliced apples, cinnamon and 5 teaspoons sugar. Set aside.
Place dry ingredients into large bowl. Make hole in dry ingredients and add wet ingredients, mixing well.
Grease angel food or Bundt pan.
Alternate layers of batter and apples, ending with batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and cool for awhile.
Then serve.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Brown flour in oil in boiling pot.
Add onions and garlic and cook until clear.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, celery and salt and pepper to suit taste.
Bring to boil and turn to simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add crab meat and shrimp and simmer 15 minutes more. Serve over rice.

title: beans 'n wieners waikiki
directions: Cut pineapple into chunks, reserving some rings for garnish. Saute green pepper, onion, pineapple and wiener chunks in margarine or butter.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce, catsup and brown sugar.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour pork and beans into baking dish.
Add pineapple mixture, stirring gently to blend.
Place halved pineapple rings on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Cook first four ingredients until hard ball stage (without stirring).
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites immediately for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over whites slowly and beat until glossy look becomes dull.
Add vanilla.
Drop on buttered pan or countertop by teaspoonfuls.

title: tuna spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and spread on assorted crackers or cucumber slices.

title: amish pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl in order given, adding the 2/3 cup water last.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake 1 hour for doneness in 350° oven.
Makes 2 large loaves or 4 small.

title: methodist church punch
directions: Make sugar into syrup using 1/2 can water; add other ingredients.
To freeze into slush, divide into 3 gallon plastic jars or bags.
Freeze 8 hours.
Add ginger ale to club soda as you pour punch into bowl.
Serves 100 people.

title: skillet zucchini combo
directions: Cut corn from cobs and set aside. Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in oil in a large skillet 5 minutes. Add zucchini; cook, stirring often, 7 minutes. Add corn, tomato and next 4 ingredients; cover and cook over low heat, stirring often, 7 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.

title: pea salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Add vinegar and salad oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Drain before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat ingredients and mix well, then put into ungreased dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Test with toothpick. Slice thin when cool.

title: biscuits(makes 12 to 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in bowl. Cut in Crisco using pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse meal. Add milk. Stir with fork until blended. Transfer dough to lightly floured surface. Knead gently 8 to 10 times. Roll dough 1/2-inch thick. Cut with floured 2-inch round cutter. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut in 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer ingredients and can be topped with cucumbers and tomatoes.
Serve at room temperature.
Can be chilled if desired.

title: saint andrew's barbecue sauce
directions: Heat the butter in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute them for 2 or 3 minutes, until an aroma is apparent. Add chili powder and jalapenos.
Saute for another 45 seconds. Add coffee, Worcestershire sauce, tomato paste, vinegar, brown sugar and cider.
Simmer for 20 minutes, or until thickens.
Keep warm until needed.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature. Combine all ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet. Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creole sauce
directions: Brown onion and pepper in the canola oil.
Add the tomatoes, pimento, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Soak cabbage for 20 minutes; drain.
Combine all ingredients, except vinegar and sugar.
Put in saucepan.
Cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add vinegar and sugar and cook 5 minutes more.

title: orange dream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients; refrigerate.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine Coca-Cola and buttermilk; set aside.
Beat butter at low speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat at low speed until blended.
Combine flour, cocoa and soda.
Add to butter mixture alternately with cola mixture; begin and end with flour mixture.
Beat at low speed just until blended.
Stir in marshmallows.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool 10 minutes.
Pour Coca-Cola Frosting over warm cake; garnish, if desired.

title: chicken meal in the crock
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and let cook all day on low setting. Ideal for working mothers!!!

title: broiled pepperoni bites
directions: Arrange bread slices on foil lined 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Broil bread about 4-inches from the heat until lightly toasted. Sprinkle half the cheese and half the onion evenly on the bread slices. Top with pepperoni. Sprinkle remaining cheese and onion evenly over the pepperoni. Broil 1 minute or until cheese is melted. Makes 15 appetizers.

title: baked perch fillets
directions: Sprinkle fish with barbecue spice and celery salt.
Place in baking dish.
Combine buttermilk, vinegar and tomato juice.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes. Serves 2.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in graham cracker crust. Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken; take off bone and break into small pieces.
Mix soups and sour cream together.
Add chicken.
Pour into casserole. Crumble crackers over top of chicken mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Place in a 350° oven until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix cauliflower, peas, cheese and Good Seasons seasoning altogether.
Put mayo on top.
Store overnight.
Then mix together before serving.

title: 7 layer dinner
directions: Preheat oven to
Brown beef and drain off excess fat. Grease pan
or
Pyrex
dish with Crisco.
Place crumbled beef in bottom of
dish.
Next
add
onion,
then
layer
with potatoes; next layer pork
and beans and then the tomato soup. Add salt and pepper over
top.
Bake for 1 to 2 hours or until potatoes
are cooked.
Remove
from
oven
and
place
sliced Velveeta cheese on top and return to oven until it melts.

title: lisa's chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken that has been cut into bite size pieces in bottom of casserole dish (9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch or larger).
Mix soups, broth and vegetables together and pour over chicken.
Now you are ready to mix the crust.
Heat the mixture together (the mixture may be runny).

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 8-inch pie plate.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in sugar and melted butter.
In small bowl, stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to butter mixture. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour in pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into wedges.
Great when topped with ice cream.

title: christmas wine
directions: Add ingredients to crock-pot.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Finish filling freezer bucket with milk.
Add 3 tsp. vanilla. Freeze as usual.

title: natural all-purpose cleaner
directions: Mix and store in marked container.

title: burritos
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Scramble eggs in skillet.
Heat tortillas on grate and put in eggs and meat; top with sauce.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook green pepper, onion, garlic clove and shortening in skillet 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, lemon juice, salt, black pepper and shrimp.
Heat and serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Into a large bowl, measure all ingredients, except egg white and walnuts.
With mixer at medium speed, beat ingredients until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl.
Pat evenly into pan.
In a cup with fork, beat egg white slightly.
Brush over top of dough and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until golden.
Immediately cut into 48 bars and remove from pan to cool on wire racks.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 48 bars.

title: brownie pie
directions: Make brownies as directed on package.
Spread batter in a greased 9-inch round layer cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into pie shaped wedges.
Top with ice cream (any flavor).
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Add yeast to 2/3 cup warm water.
Prepare milk.
Let both set. Sift dry ingredients.
Add yeast, milk and oil.
Stir together. On floured surface knead until dough is smooth (add flour if needed).
Drop by large spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Extra dough keeps two weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 12 large rolls.

title: crescent city cream "puffs"
directions: Combine water, margarine and salt in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Add flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition. Spoon dough into 10 mounds on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Remove immediately. Cool.
Prepare pudding mix as directed except using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Chill.
Fold in whipped cream, marshmallows and bananas. Cut tops from puffs. Fill with mixture.
Add tops. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: chocolate yummy
directions: Mix first three ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: rhubarb surprise cake
directions: Put all ingredients, except rhubarb, into bowl and beat well. Fold in rhubarb and pour into well-greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Over the top of batter, sprinkle 1/2 cup of chopped nuts and 1/2 cup brown sugar to cover.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Mix dry and wet ingredients separately.
Put wet ingredients in an 8-inch square greased pan.
Put dry ingredients over the wet ingredients.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cut into squares.

title: mom's potato pie
directions: Put the cottage cheese through a food processor to make it smooth.
Beat the mashed potatoes into the cottage cheese.
Then beat in the sour cream, eggs, salt and cayenne.
Stir in the scallions. Spoon into the pastry shell. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot the first day, then cold for leftovers.

title: rosebud beets and pineapple
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in vinegar and water. Cook over low heat until thick and clear, stirring often.
Do not boil hard.
Add beets and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add pineapple and heat through.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Cook 1 minute and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grandma's pork chops and beans
directions: Put pork and beans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and very little barbecue sauce.
Then put pork chops on top.
Put a little barbecue sauce on them.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in quarters, reserving juice that accumulates. Combine tomatoes, reserved juice, 1 cup stuffing mix, onion, sugar, salt, oregano and rosemary. Mix well. Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with one-fourth cup stuffing mix and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Serves 3 to 4.

title: nachos ole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan combine soup and salsa.
Cook over low heat; heat through, stirring often.
Serve over tortilla chips. Top with tomatoes, green onions, olives and peppers.
Serves 6.

title: pork chops
directions: Wash chops.
Roll in flour, salt, pepper, garlic powder and Greek seasoning.
Brown in oil in skillet real fast.
Place celery and onions in bottom of roasting pan with lid.
After pork chops are placed in pan, add 1/2 cup water, cover; bake at 300° for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: cucumbers and cream
directions: Combine vinegar, water, salt and peppercorns.
Add cucumber slices; cover and chill 2 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Gently combine cucumbers with onion and sour cream.

title: crispy peas salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill and top with crumbled bacon.

title: quick cheese sandwich
directions: Toast bread in toaster.
Place cheese on bread; top with second piece of bread.
Place on paper plate.
Microwave on High for 15 to 20 seconds, or until cheese melts.
Makes 1 serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Spread bean dip on large platter, sprinkle with ground beef. Spread with mixture of sour cream and seasoning mix, sprinkle tomatoes, green onions, black olives and cheese over the top. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine spinach, mayonnaise, sour cream, green onions, parsley, lemon juice, dill, salt and pepper.
Mix until well blended.
Refrigerate 2 hours or as long as 2 days. Serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat.
Bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool and enjoy.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Place graham crackers in a single layer in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add cereal.
Mix thoroughly and pour over graham crackers.
Melt chocolate chips and butter together and spread over cereal mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts (optional).
Let cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
They are very rich.

title: broccoli-chicken soup
directions: Cut off and discard leaves and tough parts of broccoli stalks. Wash and chop broccoli coarsely.
Add boiling water; boil until tender.
Using all the liquid, chop broccoli very fine in blender or force through sieve.
In saucepan, mix soup, cream and broccoli.
Season to taste.
Heat to simmering.
Top with croutons and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: corn salad
directions: * You may need more to get right consistency.

title: mike's gooey butter cake
directions: Mix with mixer.
Spread batter in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: chicken nicaraguense
directions: Brown chicken on both sides. Put in casserole dish. Add green pepper, celery, onion, carrots and garlic to same skillet. Cook briefly, stirring until vegetables are tender-crisp. Spoon over chicken and add the tomato juice, squash, cumin, salt and pepper. Cover and bake 50 minutes at 350° or until chicken is tender. Add the peas and bake 10 more minutes.

title: quick fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and cream in saucepan; boil 9 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat at high speed with mixer until thick.
Pour in buttered pan.
Let set.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, and salt in bowl.
In saucepan, mix water, cocoa, and margarine.
Bring to a boil, then set aside to cool.
Mix together buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour boiled cocoa mixture over sugar and flour mixture. Combine till well blended.
Add buttermilk mixture.
Pour in jelly roll pan or 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Remove from oven and ice while hot.

title: cherokee harvest salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, oil and water to a boil and pour over all.

title: peanut butter french toast
directions: Combine eggs, salt, peanut butter and milk; beat until blended.
Dip slices of bread into mixture, coating both sides. Melt butter or margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add bread slices.
Brown both sides and serve warm with honey, syrup or jelly.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Blend and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool thoroughly.

title: puffed german apple pancake
directions: Toss apple slices with 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Mix together eggs, milk, flour and salt.
In separate dish, mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: seasoned green beans
directions: Wash fresh green beans and snap thoroughly.
Remove both ends and snap in pieces to cook.
Add beans to water (enough to cover well).
Cook until tender.
I add slices of bacon that have been fried crisp and crumbled for seasoning.
Use bacon grease also. Add salt to your taste.

title: quick and easy frosting
directions: Combine ingredients and beat on medium speed with electric mixer until desired consistency, about 2 minutes.

title: california ham
directions: Put ham into a large pan filled with water, to which you add vinegar and brown sugar.
Boil 2 hours or until thermometer reaches 130° to 140°.
Let stand overnight in brine.
Remove and slice to serve.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix potatoes into mashed potatoes.
Cook hamburger and onion. Place into 2-quart casserole.
(Spray with nonstick spray.)
Layer the hamburger and onions with corn, then with mashed potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese to top and bake for 5 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
While it is baking, bring to a boil, 1 cup sugar and crushed pineapple.
Boil 5 minutes.
When cake is done, punch holes in cake and pour pineapple mixture over.
Let cool.
Prepare 1 large box vanilla pudding.
When ready to serve, spread pudding over cake, then sprinkle coconut over pudding; next a layer of bananas (sliced) and top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with pecans and cherries.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs; beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Place stick of butter in bottom of glass baking bowl.
In large bowl, mix peaches, sugar/flour mixture, vanilla and milk.
Pour over stick of butter.
Roll out biscuit dough on floured surface to about 1/4-inch thick.
Place over peach mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until crust browns.
Remove from oven and push crust down into cobbler until covered with juice.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown meat or, if fresh, cook until done.
Add vegetables; heat thoroughly.
Push meat and vegetables to the side of pan or wok; scramble eggs until done.
Add salt, pepper and season to taste. Add cooked rice; mix and heat thoroughly.
You may add soy sauce if you like (careful, it is salty!!).

title: elephant grandioso
directions: Find elephant.
Cut into bite size pieces.
(This usually takes 2 weeks.)
Season carefully and add enough gravy to cover (about 400 gallons).

title: taco pie
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; drain.
Add chili beans and simmer 15 minutes.
Add cheese when finished simmering.
While mixture is simmering, unroll crescent rolls and press them into an 8-inch pie plate.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375° on top shelf.
Pour meat, bean and cheese mixture onto pie shell and serve.
Top with salsa, shredded cheese, lettuce, tomato, sour cream, olives, etc.

title: meaty lasagna
directions: Saute onion, garlic and meat in shortening over medium heat until redness disappears, about 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and oregano.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown beef and cook with taco powder as package directions indicate.
Drain excess liquid.
Mix all ingredients and pour into an oven safe baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes (or cook in a crock-pot on low for 2 hours).
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: indian-style tandoori chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except the chicken and oil.
Place chicken pieces in yogurt marinade.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain well.
Brush with oil and cook in 375° oven for about 1 hour or until tender.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach pie triangles
directions: Defrost spinach and squeeze out excess moisture.
Simmer onions in broth until tender.
Mix onions, spinach, cheeses, herbs and seasonings.
Spray a cookie sheet with Pam.
Take two sheets phyllo dough and cut into 4 long strips.
Dab lightly with olive oil.
Put 1 heaping tablespoon spinach mix at one end of the strip.
Fold over to form a triangle over and over.
Dab olive oil on top.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Place cabbage, vinegar, water, margarine and salt in a deep cooking pot.
Cover and cook until crisp-tender, about 15 minutes, lifting and turning with a large kitchen fork 2 or 3 times.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve artificial sweetener in small amount of water. Add to cabbage slowly, lifting and mixing well.
Drain and serve.

title: mile high meringue(the 3 stages of beating are very important.)
directions: Beat egg whites into a good sized bowl. Add cold water and beat till frothy. Then add cream of tartar, vanilla and salt. Beat until stiff. Add granulated sugar and beat to stiff peaks form when beaters are lifted. Pile onto pie and be sure to spread all the way to the crust edges. Bake 12 minutes or till brown in 325° oven.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Two 8-inch square pans or one 10 x 13-inch pan may be used.

title: bean pie
directions: Soak, cook and puree beans.
(May also use 1 can of beans.) Use blender to puree.
Mix beans, sugar, milk, eggs and spices together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour, until knife in center comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip or chilled.

title: texas hill country beans
directions: Wash beans and cover with 3 inches of water.
Bring to boil. Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers; add cut up onions and bell peppers. Add whole garlic cloves and salt. Cover with cracked ice. Let stand 3 hours. Drain well.

title: hot and chili beans
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion. Saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add garlic.
Saute for 2 more minutes. Stir in tomatoes, peppers, chili powder, cumin, beans and cilantro. Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook gently for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with cornbread or over cooked elbow macaroni.
Yields 4 servings.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Place jalapeno half with oyster; wrap bacon around it and skewer onto kabob stick.
Fill sticks with a small space between each.
Grill.

title: molly's monkey bread
directions: Cut and section biscuits into quarters.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in bag.
Shake biscuit pieces in bag.
Take Bundt pan (greased) and toss biscuits in.
Melt butter and add remaining sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes and then turn pan upside down on plate and pick pieces off with fingers.

title: buttermilk scones
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°. 2. Grease a large cookie sheet and mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. 3. Add butter and rub with fingers until mixture resembles fine meal.
Wisk buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla in medium bowl to blend. 4. Gradually add flour and stir until moist crumbs form.
Turn out dough unto a lightly floured surface.
Knead 4 times to blend. 5. Transfer dough to prepared cookie sheet.
Press dough into 8-inch round.
Score dough with a sharp knife into 8 wedges. 6. Bake until golden brown (about 25 minutes).
Cool slightly then cut into 8 wedges and serve.

title: mexican salad
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain well.
Cool.
Add all ingredients together.

title: dill weed dip
directions: In mixing bowl, combine ingredients.
Blend thoroughly. Chill.
Serve with chips or veggies.

title: grilled steak sandwiches
directions: In a saucepan, heat butter, sauces, onions and salt.
Grill meat 2 or 3 minutes per side.
Top steak with heated sauce.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Put dried beef in pot and cover with boiling water; cover with lid.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Drain and blot well with paper towels to absorb excess water.
Chop fine.
Mix all remaining ingredients by hand.
Add beef, saving enough to roll ball in. Mix well.
Form ball and roll in remaining chopped beef. Refrigerate.

title: friendship bread starter
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of sugar over warm water.
Sprinkle yeast over that and let stand in a warm place to double in size or about 10 minutes.
Mix milk, sugar, flour and yeast mixture in plastic or glass container, about a 5 quart ice cream bucket size.
Stir, using wooden spoon or fork (metal retards its natural growth). Leave cover loose or place glass plate over container so it can breathe.
It doubles or even triples in size at time of vigorous rising.

title: beef-barley soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Put all ingredients in a large cooking pot.
Boil.
Turn down heat and let simmer 1 hour.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, with mayonnaise and milk last. (If you would like-cook the diced onion and celery in the cornbread.)

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edges comes out clean.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 3/4 stick margarine in casserole.
Slice squash; boil and drain.
Put 1 cup croutons in casserole with margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over 1 cup croutons.
Top with other cup of croutons and 1/4 stick margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven until done, about 45 minutes.

title: french onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until just tender.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Add bouillon and sherry.
Cook and stir until rich and bubbly.
Toss croutons with melted butter.
Add to onions along with 3/4 Swiss cheese.

title: pepper corn
directions: Cook corn according to directions and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve.

title: iowa pea salad
directions: Combine peas, cheese, celery and onion in a large bowl.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, milk, mustard, salt, pepper and hot sauce in another bowl until smooth.
Add to pea mixture; toss to coat. Refrigerate overnight.

title: bing cherry mold salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 1/2 cups of water.
Let the jello cool. Add crushed pineapple, chopped nuts and cherries.
Pour into mold. Let set several hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Heat tomato soup mix in cheese.
Let cool.
Mix unflavored gelatine with water.
Chop celery and onions.
Mix shrimp with Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in Jell-O ring greased with mayonnaise.

title: pineapple sheath cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine by spoon all ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 25 to 40 minutes. Use cream cheese icing for topping.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Combine olive oil, orange juice, salt and wine vinegar.
Add ginger or cumin and onion.
Stir to blend.
Marinate chicken in sauce for about 1 hour.
Baste chicken while cooking.
Chicken can be cooked on a grill, rotisserie or broiled in oven.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into small balls, the size of a walnut.
Flatten slightly.
Make a small indentation in the center of each cookie by using a thimble and lightly pressing the center with your thumb.
Spoon a small amount of your favorite jelly or jam into the indentation.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: flap jacks
directions: Put oil in skillet. Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Add water to make a creamy batter.
When oil is hot, drop batter into pan with tablespoon.
Fry until brown. Turn and brown on other side.
Cook on medium heat.

title: five-cup salad
directions: Combine the orange sections, pineapple chunks, coconut and marshmallows.
Blend the vanilla and sugar into yogurt and combine with fruit.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serves 4.

title: goober crisps
directions: Heat oven to
Mix
shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Blend
flour,
soda and salt; stir in.
Mix in peanuts.
Drop by
rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking
sheet.
Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Bake at 375° or until crust is brown.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Pack firmly and mold into loaf pan.
Brush with steak sauce; cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada soup
directions: In a large (2 gallon) stockpot over medium heat, combine oil, chicken base, diced onion, cumin, chili powder, garlic and cayenne pepper. Saute, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender. Place masa harina in a large saucepan over low-medium heat. Gradually add 1 quart of water, stirring constantly, to blend and remove lumps. Add masa harina mixture to onions and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer mixture 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly to eliminate the raw taste of the masa. Add remaining water to stockpot. Add tomatoes and allow mixture to return to a boil. Reduce heat to low and add cheese. Continue to simmer, stirring occasionally, until cheese melts. Remove from heat and add chicken. Ladle into serving bowls.

title: chicken italia
directions: Saute chicken and onion in butter until well browned.
Add zucchini and garlic; cook for 1 minute, then add broth, lemon juice, basil and seasonings.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice and add tomatoes.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork; garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Batter and fry pork chops about halfway done, then place in oblong baking dish. Add sliced potatoes over pork chops. Add mushroom soup. Add about 1/4 stick of margarine over soup. Cover with foil. Cook in 400° oven until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Boil spaghetti in broth.
Drain but save broth.
Mix chicken, spaghetti and remaining ingredients. Can heat on top of stove until cheese is melted or can bake in 350° oven.

title: bear casserole
directions: Layer potatoes across the bottom of a well-greased casserole (margarine).
Spread over this alternating layers of mushrooms and onions.
Pour the cream of mushroom soup over this and sprinkle with oregano, parsley flakes and paprika.
Salt and pepper to taste and top with bear meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Pour cherry pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Top with coconut and pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All liquid into pot.
Add chopped onion.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; boil until done.
Drain any excess liquid. Add mixed vegetables, cheese, mayo, sour cream, salt and pepper. Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese or crushed cracker topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix everything together.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put cracker crumbs on top (optional). Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream shortening and salt, mix in brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour, soda and baking powder. Pat out in a 9 x 13 inch pan or drop from a spoon.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Defrost berries according to package directions.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and berries, beating until light.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Place cooked shrimp in shallow baking dish.
Microwave garlic and butter in a small, glass bowl on High power for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Add crackers, wine and parsley to butter and pour over top of shrimp.
Microwave for 8 to 10 minutes at 70% power.
Garnish with additional parsley and lemon slices.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for several hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: *May use cabbage or cauliflower in place of broccoli.

title: tofu lasagne
directions: Mix water, tomato sauce and Ragu in bowl.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put a thin layer of sauce in pan.
Make a layer of uncooked lasagne noodles.
Blend together well the tofu, chopped onion and seasonings.
Make a layer of tofu mixture over noodles.
Layer spinach and olives or asparagus.
Repeat:
sauce, noodles, tofu and spinach or asparagus.
Cover with grated cheese of choice. Store in fridge overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over fish in a glass container and let stand at least 1 hour before grilling.

title: snowcapped lemon roll
directions: Step 1:
In a small mixer beat egg yolks at high speed on electric mixer until thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes. Gradually add 1/3 cup of granulated sugar, beating constantly. Stir in peel and juices.

title: frosting
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well. Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Can also add thinly sliced bananas on top of each layer of frosting.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Toss together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and chill 2 hours or more.
Bake meatballs in a shallow pan with oil in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain fat; cover with sauce.
Cook 30 minutes more.
Spoon into a chafing dish with green pepper and pineapple.
Makes about 48 meatballs.

title: meatballs
directions: Roll in small balls (about 105°).
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 7 minutes.
Put in crock-pot and add mushroom soup (don't dilute).
Cook on high for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat soup.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Add gelatin.
Cool mixture.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onions and shrimp.
Pour into mold and chill at least five hours.

title: grape-nuts dessert(good for diabetics)
directions: Put Cool Whip in a large bowl. Add Grape-Nuts (approximately 2 cups).
Let set overnight. Eat and enjoy.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: First Layer: Spread refried beans on a large platter.

title: sour cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, flour, spices and salt. Blend in sour cream and raisins.
Soak raisins in boiling water 10 minutes ahead of time.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook until thick, boil 3 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with the Brown Sugar Meringue.

title: lemon jello cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melted margarine; set aside 1/2 cup of mixture to sprinkle on top of filling.
Press the rest firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange glazed chicken tidbits
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken, mixing well.
Add chicken; toss to coat.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes, tossing chicken again after 15 minutes.
Broil for 5 minutes; turn chicken over and brush with remaining marinade.
Broil until done, about 3 minutes longer.

title: aunt betty's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, beaten egg, horseradish, salt, ketchup, milk and Lawry's seasoned salt.
Transfer mixture to a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain excess fat. Serve with gravy, mashed potatoes, vegetable, cole slaw and roll, if desired.

title: hamburger in a pea patch
directions: Combine all ingredients except the onions and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in onion rings and sprinkle with soy sauce.
Serve with salad and crackers.

title: spinach and cheese dip
directions: Blend soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir in spinach, cheese and water chestnuts.
Cover.
Chill 2 hours.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Leave chicken stand in this overnight or a couple of hours.
Keep in refrigerator.
Crush 2 cups herb seasoned croutons. Roll chicken in this.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and 1/2 cup shortening together.
Spoon half over the chicken.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Spoon remaining butter mixture over it and bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and shape into 3/4-inch meatballs.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
In saucepan, mix 1 bottle chili sauce and small jar grape jelly.
Heat and add meatballs and bring to a simmer.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Arrange chicken in baking dish. Pour mixture over top.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Serve over rice with vegetable.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, Roquefort cheese, garlic and
Worcestershire thoroughly.
Add pecans and parsley.
Roll in ball.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	cuts according to directions and drain. Saute 1/2 cup onions in 1/2 stick of butter.
Add cheese.
Mix and
turn contents
into
a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until sauce is bubbly.

title: one skillet spicy chicken 'n rice
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour and seasoned salt.
Add chicken; shake to coat well.
In large skillet, brown chicken in oil; continue cooking, uncovered, over low heat 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and chicken is cooked through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: berry or grape pie
directions: Mix water and cornstarch.
Add all other ingredients, except butter; cook until clear.
Add the butter.
Pour into cooked crust.
Cool and serve.
Top with whipped cream.
Use any kind of fruit juice.

title: cottage cheese meltaways
directions: Cream cottage cheese and butter together in a bowl.
Add flour and mix well until dough forms a ball.
Flatten into a round and wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, mixing together the sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter.
Mix the brown sugar, flour, nuts and butter together well and sprinkle on sweet potatoes for the topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix broken up cookies and next three ingredients in medium dish.
Add whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large skillet, saute onion in butter until softened.
Add next 6 ingredients and heat through. Keep warm over low heat.
Cover bottom of a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with 1/2 the enchilada sauce.
One at a time, dampen each tortilla with water and heat on both sides in a hot, ungreased skillet until soft and pliable.
Place 1/4 to 1/3 cup meat mixture on each tortilla and roll; place in a baking dish.
Repeat.
Top with remaining enchilada sauce, salsa and cheese.
Cover and bake until heated through (20 minutes).

title: huancaina sauce
directions: In a blender, add one cup of milk and one teaspoon of vegetable oil.
Add cheese, crackers and yellow pepper.
Blend and season to taste.
Huancaine sauce is most the popular entree in Peru, when served with boiled potatoes and decorate with lettuce, boiled eggs and olives.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Set aside. Cream together sugar, Crisco, eggs and bananas. Then add to the dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Then remove from pan and cool on rack.
Wrap in foil.
Store overnight at room temperature.

title: grilled shrimp with red chili, honey and garlic sauce
directions: Peel and devein shrimp and cook 3/4 the way on an open grill being sure to turn often so they do not burn or dry out.
In a separate pan place butter, garlic and chili peppers and heat on low flame. When garlic starts to brown add sherry to pan.
Turn off the flame and add honey.
Now add shrimp to saute pan and finish cooking shrimp while letting sauce reduce.
Arrange shrimp with sauce on a serving platter and sprinkle with chopped scallion.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Place sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan and cook slowly until a full boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour hot mixture over oatmeal until completely covered. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: caramel rice krispies marshmallow bars
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine and 1 1/2 packages marshmallows and pour over Rice Krispies.
Pour 3/4 of the mixture into buttered 10 x 15-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 package marshmallows.
Melt the caramels, 1/4 cup margarine and Eagle Brand milk and pour over marshmallows. Spread remaining Rice Krispies mixture over top. Cool and cut into bars.

title: creamy snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and powdered sugar. Beat in melted chocolate, milk and vanilla until smooth. Fold in marshmallows. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes or until easy to handle. Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls, then roll in coconut. Store in the refrigerator.

title: cheesy italian potatoes
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges.
Spray potato surfaces with Pam.
Combine cheese and seasonings in a small plastic bag.
Add potato wedges to the bag and shake to coat. Arrange potato slices in layers in a microwave-safe baking dish. Cover and microwave on High power for 15 minutes, rotating dish twice during cooking.

title: honeymoon salad
directions: Mix sugar, Jell-O and boiling water to dissolve.
Refrigerate until thick, but not set.
Mix cheese and pineapple until creamy, then beat with cream and Jell-O mixture.
Add pecans and pour into mold or bowl and let it set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Sift flour and soda.
Add with sour cream.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.
Remove from pan at once.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Place butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Top with coconut, then condensed milk.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips in small saucepan over low heat; spread evenly over hot coconut layer. Cool for 30 minutes.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add to other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuit coffee cake(yum!)
directions: Divide biscuits in half and put a piece of cream cheese in each, sealing the biscuit around the cheese.
Melt margarine and dip each cheese biscuit in it.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Roll each butter covered biscuit in mix.
Stand them side by side in a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle excess butter and nut mix over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sourdough machine bread
directions: Stir ingredients in order given. Cover with plastic. Let sit where warm overnight.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cider punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine 1 1/2 quarts apple juice, grape juice and lemonade concentrate; chill.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased and sugared Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Prepare pie shell, either crumb or baked pie crust.
Pour lime juice slowly in milk. Do not beat, just stir.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: stuffed peppers fiesta
directions: Remove stems and seed from peppers.
Put peppers in cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside. In a bowl combine cereal and 1/2 cup tomatoes.
Brown meat; add seasonings and mix well. Stir into cereal mixture.
Fill each pepper with 1/2 cup meat mixture.
Place in greased baking dish. Pour remaining tomatoes over peppers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: baked sausage-bean soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot oil, cook onion and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup, beans with their liquid, sausage, chilies, tomatoes with their liquid and water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes to blend flavors.

title: marshmallow cream cheese dip
directions: Mix together well.
This dip is good with fruit (apples, muskmelon, cantaloupe, watermelon, etc.).

title: cocktail pastry meatballs(makes 100)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Season with salt and pepper.
Form into small meatballs.
Blend remaining ingredients in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add meat balls.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer meatballs to dish.
Skim excess fat from sauce.
Pour over meatballs and serve warm.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar.
Drain the pineapple and strawberries and add them along with the pecans to the cream cheese and sugar mixture.
Whip the topping and fold into the cheese and fruit mixture.
Put in a pretty bowl and chill.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Mix the margarine and flour.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pudding
directions: Put butter into pan and melt.
Beat eggs until light.
Mix with other ingredients and bake, stirring while baking.
Bake about 45 minutes in iron skillet.

title: spicy chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets with butter.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter with the black pepper, cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Beat in the egg and the vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa. Add the sifted ingredients, 1/2 cup at a time, to the batter, mixing well after each addition.
Shape the dough into 1 inch balls.
Place them 2 inches apart on the prepared cookie sheets. Dip the bottom of a glass into confectioners sugar, then use it to flatten the balls to a thickness of 1/4 inch.
Bake for 12 minutes or until the edges of the cookies are lightly browned.

title: no-bake chocolate raspberry cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into spring-form pan, halfway up the sides.
Chill.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Place peeled eggs in gallon-container with tight lid.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over eggs.
Refrigerate at least 2 days before serving.

title: cathy's coconut mousse
directions: Beat all of the first 6 ingredients until thick and creamy. Add coconut flaked and fold in.
Spoon into cupcake liners in muffin (cupcake) pan.
Top with half of maraschino cherries as optional.
Store in freezer at least 3 hours.
Keep frozen until ready to eat.
Makes about 24.

title: grilled salmon oriental
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry.
Arrange fish in rectangular non-aluminum baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir and pour over steaks, turning to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine; add rice and 1 1/4 cups water.
Add dry onion soup; mix well.
Cut up chicken into pieces and add to 1 cup of water and mix.
Turn skillet on low and cook, covered, about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bessie b's crab dip
directions: Soften the cheese and slowly blend in soup so that there are no lumps.
Stir in mayonnaise, lemon juice, garlic and Worcestershire.
(Can be made the day before to this point.)
One hour before serving, pick over drained crab to be sure all bones are out.
Add to soup mixture. Keep cold until serving.
Serve with dipping chips.

title: almost like heaven cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. While warm, put holes in it and pour pineapple over it.
Let cake cool, then make instant pudding.
Add cream cheese and beat.
Pour this on cake, then spread Cool Whip.
Can sprinkle with pecans or coconut.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Crumble together and press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool. Slice 6 or 7 bananas on top of crust.

title: campfire soup
directions: Cook onion, celery and cabbage in water in stock pot until the onion and celery are clear.
Add tomato juice, Veg-All and Worcestershire sauce and cook 10 minutes.
Add hamburger, salt and pepper.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Mix all ingredients. Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Spread cashews and noodles on cookie sheet and heat them in oven.
Meanwhile, slowly heat and melt butterscotch chips.
When melted, add nuts and noodles and mix well.
Quickly drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper and let them cool on counter.

title: salmon sausage
directions: Mix the salmon with corn meal until proper consistency to mix into cakes.
Fry in hot fat; salt to taste.

title: hot punch
directions: Pour juices in a 36 cup coffee maker.
In basket, put 2 cinnamon sticks and a few red hots.
Let it perk.

title: fruit salsa
directions: Spray 2 flour tortilla shells with butter flavored Pam. Cut with pizza cutter into triangles or strips. Put into large bowl with a seal and sprinkle with 1 1/2 tablespoons of cinnamon and sugar. Shake in sealed bowl until coated. Bake on nonstick sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: tom's "hurtin" chili
directions: In large saucepan (6-quart), place meat and saute.
Add peppers, onions, garlic and vinegar.
Saute until soft.
Add spices and beans; simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and bouillon and stir well.
Simmer 1 hour (until meat is tender). Serve over white rice!!

title: cola cake
directions: Using a saucepan, combine Coca-Cola, butter, oil and cocoa. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Let melt.
Combine flour, sugar and soda in bowl.
Combine buttermilk, beaten eggs and vanilla in another bowl.

title: lindsey's german oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put butter in 8-inch pie plate.
Place in oven to melt.
Keep an eye on it and remove when melted.
Don't let butter burn.
Beat eggs until fluffy in large bowl.
Add milk, flour and salt and beat until smooth.
Pour immediately into hot pie plate.
Bake for 18 minutes.
Don't peek!
Top with butter, pancake syrup or powdered sugar.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare apples and set aside.
Measure salad oil into large bowl.
Add sugar and eggs and beat on low speed of mixer until creamy.
Sift flour and measure.
Sift again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add flour mixture a little at a time and beat well.
Fold in apples, pecans and vanilla.
Batter will be stiff. Spread evenly in a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Can be served plain or with whipped topping.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green pepper.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer.

title: leftover potato patties
directions: Saute onion in oil until golden.
Combine with potatoes and shape into small, flat patties.
Roll in flour and brown both sides in oil or bake on greased cookie sheet in moderate oven until brown.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package; drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter; stir in flour, stirring until smooth, but not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft over low heat (do not brown).
Add reserved liquid, stirring constantly to avoid lumping; add seasoning and cheese which has been cut into small pieces. Stir until smooth and melted.
Combine spinach.
This may be served immediately or put into a casserole dish and topped with buttered bread crumbs.
Flavor increases if later is done.
Can be frozen.

title: meat and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles. Cook, but do not brown celery and onion in butter.
Add meat, soup, salt and pepper; heat thoroughly.
Pour half of noodle in 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with half mixture. Repeat layers with the rest of noodles and mixture.
Top with cheese and bake at 375°
for 30 minutes until bubbly hot and brown.
Serves 6.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.

title: sesame noodles
directions: Blend first 9 ingredients.
Pour over scallions and cooked spaghetti.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: In skillet, cook zucchini and onion in oleo until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in seasonings.
In bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in zucchini; mix.
Separate dough, place in ungreased 11-inch quiche, 10-inch pie pan or 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour in zucchini mix.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: mama's turkey stew
directions: Remove skim from turkey thighs. Remove bones from meat.

Cut meat into small bite size pieces. Brown turkey on top of stove in oil in a large deep cooking pot. Add onion and water and cook (not boil) until meat is tender but not cooked thoroughly. Add potatoes and carrots. Cook until potatoes are done. Add peas and diced tomatoes. Add Gravy Boat.
Mix/stir until all is brown in color. Mix cornstarch with small amount of water.
Add to bubbling mixture until thick.
You may need more water for a "loose" stew. Serves 4.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Soak kidney beans overnight with baking soda (2 teaspoons) and salt.
In a teaspoon of bacon grease cook celery, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add cooked ingredients to beans covered with a good amount of water.
Add bay leaf, cayenne pepper, thyme and 2 tablespoons Tony Chachere Cajun seasoning.
Add cut up regular and Cajun sausage.
Let simmer for 1 or 2 hours.
Cook bacon, save grease, crumble bacon and set aside.
Add flour, water and 1 cup mashed beans to bacon grease.
Put this mixture back in beans.
Add cayenne flakes and 1 cup catsup and simmer for 1 hour.
Cook rice and serve the red beans over the rice.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook beans as directed.

About 45 minutes before beans are fully cooked, add onion, carrots and cabbage. Continue cooking for 30 minutes. Add tomato juice and whole black pepper. Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes. Salt to taste.

title: coq au vin
directions: Wash chicken and dry on paper towels. In Dutch oven, saute bacon until crisp; remove. Add butter and drippings; heat. Add chicken and brown well all over; remove. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat from Dutch oven.

Add mushrooms and white onions to Dutch oven; cook until nicely browned. Remove. Set aside with chicken. Add green onion and garlic to Dutch oven; saute 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and thyme. Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until the flour is browned, takes about 3 minutes. Gradually stir in wine and chicken broth; bring to boiling, stirring. Stir in bacon, chicken pieces, onions and mushrooms. Refrigerate covered overnight. Next day, add scrubbed potatoes. Bake, covered, at 400° for one hour and 50 minutes (or until tender). Garnish with parsley. Makes 4 servings.

title: quick vegetable manicotti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with no-stick cooking spray.

title: delicious banana pudding
directions: Mix instant vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups cold milk, sugar, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas in large bowl.
Pour mixture over them.
Cool!

title: ham, cheese, potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat cheese and cream, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining stuff.
Cover; bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Mix other ingredients and drop from spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Boil
sugar,
syrup and oleo
for 1 minute. Remove from heat and
add
peanut butter and corn flakes.
Press in square pan. Cool and cut.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Drain liquid from sauerkraut, cut with scissors.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Will keep many weeks in refrigerator.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix pineapple with juice and sugar. Bring to a boil. Add dry jello and water; stir well and let gel. Add cheese, pecans, and Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in a closed container and refrigerate. Drink 2 ounces a day.

title: mom's $300 cake (red velvet cake)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and beat well. Make paste with cocoa and food coloring.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Sift salt and flour; add alternately with 3/4 cup buttermilk.
Mix well.
Mix vinegar and soda with remaining buttermilk; fold into first mixture.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all until well blended; shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.
These may be frozen and baked when needed. Great for parties!

title: chop stick tuna
directions: Combine.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and taco seasoning.
Mix lettuce, tomato, onion, green pepper, black olives and beef.
Just before you serve, add dressing, cheese and chips.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add sour cream; blend and knead lightly.
Pat or roll out and cut.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Yields 16 biscuits.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix with the jello. Add the water, oil, eggs and 1/2 of the strawberries.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or jelly roll pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. Ice while warm.

title: sausage, egg and cheese casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place bread or grits in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together; pour over the casserole.
May cover and sit overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bread (sesame braid)
directions: Let bread dough rise (approximately 1 1/2 loaves of the frozen kind).
Break off pieces the size of hickory nuts.
Roll in melted butter and then in 1 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Drop in greased tube pan (must be tube pan; other will not work).
Let rise until size of walnuts.
Start at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce to 350° for 15 minutes, for a total of 30 to 40 minutes.
Invert and remove from pan and pluck-it!

title: cherry breeze
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Place in 9 x 9-inch pan or pie dish. Press in bottom of pan.
Refrigerate crust while mixing other ingredients. Beat cream cheese, lemon juice, vanilla and Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour, then spread cherry pie filling over top.
Continue to refrigerate until serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large (very large) kettle, mix everything with enough water to make a good soup.
Simmer and serve.
Can freeze some for a later date.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix all ingredients except bread crumbs together.
Place mixture in an ovenproof container.
Mixture may be refrigerated at this point until needed.

title: california dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and cream; add other ingredients. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: fresh peach torte
directions: Day Before:
Preheat oven to 275°.
Beat eggs with salt until frothy.
Add sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, then add vinegar and vanilla.
Beat 10 minutes.
Cut 2 (9-inch) circles from brown paper.
Spread 1/2 of meringue on each circle.
Place circles on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let cool in oven.
When cool, store in covered container.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain on paper towels, then crumble up.
Flatten biscuits.
Brush with melted margarine.
Top with sausage and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° approximately 10 minutes on a cookie sheet.
Serve hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in a large skillet in olive oil.
Place rice in ungreased shallow 3 quart baking dish.
Pour orange juice over rice.
Top with pork chops.
Pour soup over all.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes until pork chops are done and rice is tender.

title: pimento cheese deluxe
directions: Mix all together to desired consistency.

title: beef pastry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a large mixing bowl, combine and mix well all the ingredients.

title: creamy cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Saute celery, onion and carrots in butter in a large soup kettle for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and chicken broth.
Add cauliflower and simmer until tender.
Mix flour in milk until smooth; add pepper and mustard and add broth.
Add cheese and bacon.
Stir until melted and blended.
Do not boil.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pastry for one 9-inch pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until particles are small pea size.
Sprinkle in water tossing with a fork until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans inside of bowl.
One or 2 tablespoons more water may be added, if necessary.
Roll dough in a ball and flatten round on lightly floured cloth board.
Roll pastry 2 inches larger than inverted pie plate with cloth covered rolling pin.
Fold pastry in quarters and place in a pie plate. Unfold and ease into plate.
Press firmly into plate.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a well-greased pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Cut all ingredients fine.

title: sugar free spice cake
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups of the water and raisins in a small Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Boil until water is evaporated or absorbed by the raisins.
Remove from heat.
Add applesauce, eggs, Sugar Twin, oil and remaining 1/2 cup of water.
Stir until well combined.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and soda.
Gradually add to applesauce mixture with vanilla; stir well.
Spoon batter into 10-inch Bundt pan, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut flour and Crisco together with knife until pea size.
Then add ice water.
Shape into round ball.
Roll out in 9 or 10-inch circle.
Put in pie plate and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Combine ingredients and toss with mayonnaise to taste. Refrigerate before serving.
Serve with rye bread.

title: chili rellenos dish
directions: Layer in 13 x 13 x 13-inch greased baking dish 1 layer green chilies and 1 layer grated cheese.
Rotate until chilies and cheese are used up.
Mix eggs, milk and flour; pour over chilies and cheese.

title: peanutty-crunch pie
directions: In
bowl
mix
peanut butter and corn syrup until thoroughly combined.
Add
Rice
Krispies; mix until well coated. Press mixture evenly and firmly around sides and in bottom of buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Chill until firm.	Spread ice cream evenly
in pie shell.	Freeze until firm.
Cut into wedges to serve; top with peach slices or other fresh fruit.	Serves 8.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock pot and heat on low until all ingredients are melted and mixed.
Serve warm with Triscuit or Ritz crackers.

title: admonition cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box; cool.
Split into 4 layers.
Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut; refrigerate overnight.
Ice cake and wrap well.
Refrigerate for at least 5 days before cutting. You are admonished not to use sooner.
Freezes well after 5 days. This is messy to ice but is delicious.

title: shanghai ham
directions: Sear and scald the pork by soaking it in boiling water to cover for a few minutes.
When the water returns to a boil, drain and rinse with cold water.
Place pork with all ingredients in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer. Turn pork occasionally until tender, about 2 hours.
Remove cover and increase heat.
Baste pork until about 1 cup of liquid remains, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Skim fat and serve.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl; stir in boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour oil in a depth of 1/2-inch in a large skillet.
Use a tablespoon dipped in hot water.
Drop cornmeal mixture into hot oil.
Fry over medium heat 1 minute on each side or until golden.
Drain on paper towel.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Spread flour mixture on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato salad vinaigrette
directions: Place potatoes in large saucepan.
Cover with cold water; add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil, covered, over high heat. Reduce heat; simmer until barely tender, 15 to 20 minutes (do not overcook).
Drain.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into mixture of flour, salt and sugar. Mix water, vinegar and egg. Add to flour mixture. Stir until well mixed. Divide dough into 4 or 5 parts. Roll out thin and use what you need, then freeze any leftover dough. May be thawed and rolled out for quick pies at a later date.
Makes 4 or 5 crusts.

title: cheesy-potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain most of the water off. Stir butter and green onions into the hot potatoes.
Mix together the Milnot, soups and milk and pour over potatoes.
Add crumbled bacon and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low until ready to serve.

title: lickety-split vegetable dip
directions: In blender, process yogurt, cottage cheese, dried onion flakes, garlic powder, dill weed, sugar and salt until creamy. Pour into containers; cover and chill to blend flavors.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water to a hard ball stage.
Do not stir once it starts boiling.
Add vinegar; do not stir.
Add syrup mixture slowly to beaten eggs as you continue to beat.
Add vanilla and nuts; beat with a wooden spoon until you can drop it on wax paper or foil without it "running."
Spoon mixture onto paper.

title: paper thin pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with salt and 1 gallon boiling water.
Stir each day for 7 days.
Drain and with 1 gallon boiling water and 2 tablespoons powdered alum, let stand 24 hours.
Drain and mix in vinegar, sugar and pickling spices.
Boil and pour over cucumbers. Let stand 4 days.
Each day, drain off syrup and boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Pack in jars.
Pour hot syrup over pickles in jars, then seal.

title: butterscotch torte(also chocolate torte using chocolate pudding)
directions: First Layer:
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar, flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: Stir soup mix in package before measuring.
Lightly brown ground beef, drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, frozen vegetables, celery, onion soup mix and sugar. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Combine mustard, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Stir in water chestnuts and vegetables.
Spoon into an ungreased 2-quart casserole; sprinkle cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and heat thoroughly. Do not boil.
Makes about 4 servings.
For even better flavor, add some cheese, crumbled up bacon and sauteed onions.

title: sugar-free chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Make pudding, using 3 cups cold milk.
Beat approximately 2 minutes.
Add sugar-free peanut butter to taste.
(I usually use 1/2 to 3/4 cup).
Can add cream cheese or leave out.
Fold in 1 small container of Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth and chill.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Combine.
Mash, knead and squeeze "until you feel better" and until there are no lumps of margarine.
Next, form the dough into small balls, not as big as a walnut, and put on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding and juice of pineapple.
Drain fruit cocktail and oranges.
Add fruit to Cool Whip.
Mix pudding and fruit. Refrigerate one hour before serving.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl and chill until ready to use.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms - pull stems and shop stems and fry with sausage.
Drain.
Crush stuffing mix with a rolling pin.
Mix stem and sausage with stuffing mixture and cheese.
Spoon in mix to mushroom caps.
Pile high and microwave on high for 3 minutes on a paper towel.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat thoroughly.
In large cooker, add meat and water; heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. If desired, thicken stew.
In covered jar, shake 1 cup cold water and 2 to 4 tablespoons flour until blended.
Stir into stew; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine milk and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Stir in lemon juice.
Blend well.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff.
Spread over pie. Chill.

title: moravian slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, carrots and green pepper.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed; heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together until smooth butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs.
Gradually add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop batter by well rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields 7 to 8 dozen.

title: spicy hot rutabagas
directions: Cut up bacon; saute in large stewer until tender.
Pour in diced rutabagas.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour water on top; let come to a boil, then lower to medium heat.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: oven baked beans
directions: Mix all together. Pour into 1-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes or until thickened. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream butter until smooth.
Add sugar, gradually, beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add creamed mixture alternately with mix; beat until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 4 (9-inch) layer pans, greased and lined on bottom with greased paper.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.
(If you only have 2 pans, bake 1/2 of batter at a time.)
After removing cakes from oven, let stand 5 minutes, then turn out on racks to cool.
Spread Lane Frosting between layers on top and sides of cake.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all but last ingredient together.
