Add mayonnaise and chill for 1/2 hour, then serve.
Serves 4.

title: hearty soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large pot. Drain.
Add seasonings and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes. Stir occasionally. Soup becomes thinner as it cooks. Great with cornbread.

title: donna's strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In a bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add berry mixture to the dry ingredients; stir until well blended.
Add nuts, if using, and stir again.
Pour into pans.
Bake for about 1 hour, or until knife comes out clean.

title: frito pie casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add taco seasoning (following instructions on package). Add mushrooms and onion. Simmer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: susie's chicken and artichokes
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and paprika.
Brown in a large skillet with butter.
When brown, remove to a large 9 x 13-inch baking dish in which you have a layer of chopped and drained artichokes. Lay chicken on top.

title: chinese salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and mix with sugar.
Put veggies in a large glass jar and pour vinegar over them.
Seal and refrigerate.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch plastic flowerpot lined with aluminum foil.

title: steak round up
directions: Cut steak into strips; dip in seasoned flour and roll up. Wrap a strip of bacon around each roll and secure with a toothpick.
Brown steak rolls over medium heat in hot oil.
Pour off excess grease.
Add soup and water.
Cover; simmer for one hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Slightly beat the eggs.
Mix everything else together.
Pour into the pie shell.
Cut the butter in pads and put on top of the pie.
Cook at 350° until firm on top, approximately 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread, place in greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Brown and drain sausage in skillet.
Spoon sausage over bread. Sprinkle with one cup cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: firehouse chili
directions: Brown ground chuck in large Dutch oven.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, water and chopped onion to ground chuck.
Combine chili powder, red pepper, garlic powder, cumin, salt, paprika and oregano.
Add to other ingredients.
Add red kidney beans, if desired.
Cook over medium to low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with grated Cheddar cheese on top of each serving.

title: layered taco dip
directions: This should be prepared night before and placed in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease bread pans.
Makes two large or three small breads. Cream butter.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients and beat well.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook white beans in water to cover in saucepan until almost done, soft but not mushy.
Drain off almost all water.
Combine beans with all other ingredients and place in a bean pot, 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish or a slow cooker.
Bake in oven at 300° for 2 to 3 hours, uncovered.
In slow cooker, heat on low overnight.
Use bean pot directions for baked beans.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and whip.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell until firm.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix dry ingredients until well blended.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 10 x 13 pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini-crusted pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Salt zucchini lightly and let it sit for 15 minutes.
Squeeze out all excess moisture.
Combine all crust ingredients and spread into an oiled 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until surface is dry and firm.
Brush top with oil and broil it, under moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Pile all your favorite pizza toppings on (tomato sauce, olives, sauteed mushrooms, strips of peppers, lots of cheese, etc.) and heat whole mess in 350° oven for about 25 minutes.
Serve hot, cut into squares, with big tossed salad.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: preacher's cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, baking soda, vanilla, eggs, nuts, and pineapple with juice.
Pour into 9x13x2 inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 300 degree oven for 30 to 45 minutes, or until done. Frost if desired.
Yield:
1 (9x13 inch) cake.

title: oatmeal-chip cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water, onion and butter to a boil.
Add broccoli; bring to a boil again.
Remove from heat; add rice.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in a casserole; bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: fried flounder fillet
directions: Roll flounder in flour.
Put butter or oil in skillet.
Add floured fillets.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and cook over low flame 10 minutes on each side.
Remove from pan; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Serves 4.

title: corn dressing
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Can add sausage.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Do not use mixer!
Combine dry ingredients and sift together into large mixing bowl.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir until well mixed, but do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or in one Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Marinate overnight, flipping occasionally.
Simmer in Dutch oven, covered, for 1 hour.

title: dumplins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out thin.
Cut into squares.
Drop in boiling broth and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar to boiling; remove from heat and add oil.
Pour over ingredients.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: baked apples
directions: Make enough to fill 6 apples.
Core apples, stuff with mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Pour maple syrup over tops before baking.
Use warm apple cider on top before serving.

title: fried rice
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: olive garden fettucine alfredo
directions: In large saucepan combine cream cheese, parmesan, butter and milk, stirring constantly until smooth.
Toss pasta lightly with sauce, coating well.
Leftovers freeze well.

title: double chocolate whip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in blender until smooth.
Float chocolate sprinkles on top of each serving.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: You may use 1/2 to 1 cup of broth in the soup mixture for a thinner pie.

title: ranch house round steak
directions: Cut meat in serving size pieces.
Trim excess fat.
Slash edges of meat to prevent curling.
Combine flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with mixture.
(Set aside any remaining flour mixture.)
In heavy skillet, brown meat on both sides in the hot oil.
(If necessary, use 2 skillets or brown meat half at a time.)
Add reserved flour mixture to skillet.
Combine water and Worcestershire.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Cover tightly. Cook over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat to platter.
Pour pan juices over and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cold pickles
directions: Put all in gallon jar and mix well.
Add sliced pickles.
Put in refrigerator for 3 days.
Shake once a day.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Grate them on fine grater.
Quickly stir in onions, eggs, flour and salt.
Drop in deep fat and fry until brown.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Put catsup, sugar and salt in blender.
Add oil and vinegar alternately.
Blend 5 minutes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: sopapilladallas, texas
directions: Add water gradually to dry mixture until all dry ingredients are used, kneading until it forms a ball.

title: marshmallow date roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except graham cracker crumbs, until well blended. Form into logs and roll in graham cracker crumbs. Wrap in wax paper and
refrigerate overnight. slice into 3/4 inch pieces. Serve cold.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over cut up chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Put pork and onion through food chopper.
Add salt, pepper, sage, thyme and rice.
Wilt cabbage leaves in boiling water, 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain leaves; put rice and meat mixture inside cabbage leaf.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish and pour in seasoned tomatoes over stuffed leaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: aunt janice's homemade caramels(when you have plenty of time!)
directions: In a large double boiler, bring the first 4 ingredients to a slow boil, stirring constantly (use a medium burner).
Slowly add evaporated milk, keeping the boiling constant and continually stirring, until 248° on a candy thermometer is reached.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour all into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
As cooled, wrap caramel in bite size pieces, using wax paper as the wrap.

title: zucchini meat loaf
directions: In large bowl mix first 8 ingredients.
Set aside.
Add garlic and zucchini slices to hot oil and saute 10 minutes on medium heat.
Put 1/2 mixture meat into 8-inch greased square pan.
Top with layer of sauteed zucchini, cover with remaining meat mixture. Top with tomato sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican party dish
directions: Cover ground beef in water,using deep pot. Boil 30 minutes (do not drain).
Add all other ingredients and cook 30 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish; use chips to dip or serve.
Better made a day or two in advance.

title: cabbage delight
directions: Fry bacon in
medium
pot.
Add rest of ingredients and cook on medium heat until tender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with rolls or biscuits. Sprinkle sausage over rolls; add cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat with mixer about 10 minutes.
Make a mixture of brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Spread 1/2 of the cake mixture in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nut mixture.
Spread rest of cake mixture over; top with remaining nut mixture.
Marbleize with knife and bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel and slice potatoes. Mix brown sugar and seasonings; sprinkle over potatoes. Dot with butter; cover. Place over low heat. Cook 30 minutes. Remove cover the last 5 minutes to thicken syrup. Turn potatoes to glaze. Yield: 8 servings.

title: chicken bog(serves 20 to 30)
directions: Cook chicken
and
debone; save broth.	Dice onions and cut bacon
into
1-inch
strips
and
saute
together in large cooking pot.
Add chicken broth, 2 cups broth per cup of rice. May add little water if not enough of chicken broth.
Bring to boil and add
rest
of ingredients.	Turn down on low heat and cook until rice is fluffy and done.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Combine wet ingredients.
Stir wet into dry until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: turkey salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together soup and mayonnaise until smooth. Put in turkey, celery, red pepper, onions, parsley and pepper. Makes about 5 cups.

title: mexican crinkles
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into balls and roll in additional granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350°.
(If using all-purpose flour, add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon baking powder.)
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Mix until smooth.
Frost cake and top with nuts, if desired.

title: supreme pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and cool.
Add dressing and seasoning.
Toss with an assortment of chopped fresh vegetables.
Chill.

title: philadelphia tangy chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Fry in butter until browned.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over chicken. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage
directions: Fry bacon.
Clean and cut up the cabbage.
Wash the cabbage and put it in the pot with the bacon and drippings.
Cook with high heat, constantly stirring, until all cabbage pieces are coated with bacon drippings.
Lower heat and cook until just tender but still crisp.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O in boiling water, add cream cheese and blend in
blender
(if you have one) until well blended.
Add pineapple, vanilla
and
sugar;
mix,
then
add Seven-Up and pecans.
Mold in a large container.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch dish or
large
mold. Very good.
(If I don't have Seven-Up, I use Sprite and that's very good also.) Also good with lime Jell-O.

title: green glop
directions: Mix all ingredients and thoroughly chill for five minutes.

title: for children clay play dough
directions: Add water to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add cake coloring for variety.
Refrigerate.
Good for rainy day entertainment.

title: brunswick stew by gary
directions: This is an old family recipe and will take a lot of your time, however, it will be worth your efforts.
So relax and put on your favorite blues c.d. and get going!

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix together drained fruits.
Add cream cheese mixture. Fold in Dream Whip. Refrigerate.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sunshine cake
directions: First beat egg whites stiffly, then beat in cream of tartar. Next, put in sugar and flour; just mix with a big spoon.
Last, add egg yolks.

title: spiced peach souffle salad
directions: Drain peaches, chop and set aside.
Heat peach liquid to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in this liquid.
Chill until consistency of egg white.
Chill milk until it begins to freeze. When gelatin thickens, stir in peaches, celery, pecans and mayonnaise.
Whip milk and lemon juice and add to mixture.

title: old fashioned molasses fruit cake
directions: Beat sugar, shortening, molasses and eggs together.
Sift 3 cups flour with dry ingredients.
Mix flour mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in more flour until stiff.
Put out in 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 or 5 layers.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Bake in 400° oven in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or large iron skillet.

title: huckleberry delight
directions: Mix together the berries, water, sugar and corn starch and cook until thickened, let cool.
Beat cream cheese into dream whip and spread over crust.
Top with huckleberry mix, chill.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown steak in shortening.
Place steak in 3-quart casserole. Arrange potatoes, carrots, onions and tomatoes over meat in casserole.
Add flour, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and liquid from tomatoes to shortening.
Pour over vegetables and cover.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 6.

title: the mountain dip(nacho style)
directions: How to Microwave the Mountain: Crumble beef into 2-quart casserole dish. Stir in 1/2 cup of salsa, onion salt, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Cover. Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes, or until beef is no longer pink, stirring once or twice to break apart. Drain; stir in remaining 1/2 cup salsa and beans. On a platter, mound mixture into a rounded shape, about 9-inches.

title: whatever dish(30 minute dish)
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Cook macaroni and drain. Combine beef and macaroni with tomato in baking dish.
Grate cheese over top and place in oven at 350°.
Cook until cheese melts and serve with any meal.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
using broth to reach desired consistency.
Sprinkle
a
little flour into mixture and blend well.
Add	chicken as desired, either picked or whole pieces. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: black cow
directions: Into a chilled 10-ounce glass, pour the chilled root beer. Top with generous scoop of slightly softened vanilla ice cream. Serve immediately.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Roll into 3 logs.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: In an ungreased shallow baking dish or pie plate, combine the first 5 ingredients. Top with pepperoni and olives. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with rye chips, crackers or vegetables. Yield: 24 servings.

title: one minute fudge frosting
directions: Combine all together in pan.
When it starts to boil, time 1 minute.
Take from stove and let cool before beating.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
You may add 1/4 cup peanut butter and beat while hot.

title: puppy chow for people(yields 40 servings)
directions: Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until melted, stirring to mix well. Pour over cereal in large bowl; mix to coat well.
Combine with confectioners sugar in large paper bag.
Shake until cereal is evenly coated.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add milk; beat 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice; beat another 2 minutes.
Pour into pie crust; chill until firm.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook package of broccoli.
Saute chopped onion in 1/2 stick of oleo.
On bottom of casserole dish, combine Minute rice (uncooked), water, milk, soup and cheese (cut in small pieces). Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until crust forms.

title: black-eyed pea's lucky dip
directions: Melt margarine and both cheeses in a casserole dish in the microwave.
Drain the black-eyed peas and save the liquid.
Gently mash the peas with a fork.
Stir peas, garlic, onion and jalapenos into melted cheese mixture.
Add the liquid saved from the peas to the mixture if it is too thick.
Serve warm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute garlic, onion and parsley in olive oil until onion is translucent.
Add canned tomatoes and sugar.
Simmer on medium-low heat for approximately 2 hours, uncovered, until desired thickness is reached.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit bowl supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill for about 1 hour. Serve as a dessert or as a salad on crisp salad greens.
Makes 6 cups or 12 servings.
You may also use one (16 ounce) can of fruit cocktail.
Drain this well also.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Mix well and put in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers in a bowl and mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle cracker mixture on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine and stir until melted. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1 cup chopped pecans. Pour into buttered square pan. Cool before cutting into squares.

title: banana fritters
directions: Beat together first eight ingredients.
Batter should be smooth and the consistency of pancake batter.
Heat two inches of oil to 375°.
Dip banana chunks into the batter and drop them into the hot oil.
Fry for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm, sprinkled with confectioners sugar.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cover apples with water and add sugar. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until cooked almost to preserves. Roll out biscuits on floured surface until very thin. Put 1 spoon of apples on half of rolled out biscuit. Add a pat of butter and some pecans. Pat around edges of biscuit dough with water; fold over and seal by pressing edges with a fork. Fry in hot oil until biscuit dough is golden brown.

title: very special apple cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Cream oil and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs. Then add dry ingredients.
Add apples and pecans last.
Grease and flour tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool completely in pan before removing.

title: cheddar cheese balls
directions: Grate cheeses in blender and mix everything together by hand. Form into 2 large balls.
Roll in nuts (slivered almonds on Saran Wrap), then wrap around the cheese ball and chill.
Good for parties or Christmastime.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water.
Stir the mayonnaise into the gelatin after slightly set.
Mix all ingredients as stated.
Chill until firm.

title: mushroom tarts
directions: Melt butter.
Cook onion and mushrooms until all moisture has evaporated.
Remove pan from heat.
Sprinkle flour over mushrooms; stir well.
Add cream; bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Fill tiny shells made from your favorite pie crust recipe.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in water until tender.
Skin and debone.
Saute chopped onions and green pepper in butter.
Add chicken stock to soup mixture.
Place chicken, onions, pepper, rice and Worcestershire sauce in greased 2-quart casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour stock mixture over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese, bake 5 minutes longer.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, milk and (if desired) salt.
Over medium low heat, cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
In small bowl, using whisk, lightly beat egg yolks.
Add small amount of milk mixture to yolks.
Blend well.
Stir yolks into saucepan until blended.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Allow custard to cool slightly.
Meanwhile, cut bananas crosswise. Place slices on bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange layers of vanilla wafers.
Top with layer of custard, then bananas.
Repeat layering twice.
Top with meringue.
Cook in oven until meringue browns.
Let cool and serve.

title: pudding pops
directions: Prepare the pudding according to directions.
Quickly pour the pudding into small paper cups and insert a popsicle stick.
Put cups into a freezer and enjoy the next day.

title: crock-pot mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes with just enough milk to mash easy. Add salt, pepper, butter, cream cheese and sour cream.
Cool (even overnight).
Put in crock-pot (greased) and cook on low for 4 hours.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each. Add flour and milk alternately. Add vanilla and baking powder.
Pour into greased Bundt or tube pan. Place in cold oven. Turn heat to 325° and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, longer if necessary. Cool and remove from pan.

title: garden pea casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except crackers.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Place in casserole and cover with crushed crackers.
Bake 30 minutes until bubbly at 350°.

title: peter paul cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box. Cool on cake rack.
Split layers.
Mix sugar and milk in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add marshmallows, coconut and vanilla. Spread between layers.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken and seasonings into 3-quarts water and cook until tender.
Debone.

title: bacon and cheese oven omelet(5 to 6 servings)
directions: Cook bacon; drain and curl one slice.
Chop 4 slices and leave others whole.
Cut cheese slices into halves.
Arrange in bottom of lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Beat together eggs and milk with fork.
Add chopped bacon.
Pour over cheese and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Arrange whole bacon slices on top and curl in middle.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
Combine buttermilk and soda; stir until soda dissolves.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Add 1 1/2 cups walnuts and coconut, stirring well.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool layers in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring to a boil water, cinnamon and cloves.
Boil 15 minutes. Add sugar and tea bags; let steep 5 minutes (off heat).
Add orange, lemon and pineapple juice.
Mix.
Reheat and serve.

title: "dump st." chicken
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour over chicken breasts in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
This is a quick, easy recipe.
The chicken breasts should be rinsed in cold water and blotted dry before putting into baking pan.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Thoroughly mix all together.
May use more milk if desired but add gradually and mix well.

title: frozen dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and oleo.
Cut like cornmeal.
Add boiling water.
Mix and cool.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apple and sugar.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Beat well eggs, oil and vanilla; add to apple mixture.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, raisins and nuts to apple mixture.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour, angel food pan for 1 hour or 2 loaf pans for 35 minutes.

title: six-layered dinner
directions: In 3-quart casserole, layer in order given, starting with potatoes and ending with beef.
Salt and pepper each layer to taste.
Pour tomatoes and juice over casserole.
Cook, covered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are done.
Serve with green salad.

title: champ
directions: Champ is an Irish dish introduced to me by a family from Ballymurphy, Belfast, Northern Ireland.

title: wild and cheesy chicken
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Melt butter; add onions, celery and pepper.
Saute gently until tender.
Mix with other ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and 1 teaspoon of salt in boiling water for 10 minutes; drain and add 1/2 stick margarine.
Grate cheese; add to macaroni.
Beat eggs and milk so as not to curdle eggs, then add to macaroni.
Add salt and pepper; stir all together.
Butter a large dish; pour macaroni mixture in.
Cook at 400° in oven for 35 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken
directions: Cut peppers in strips; then saut in 2 to 3 tablespoons oil until tender.
Remove from pan.
Cook chicken in same pan with oil.
When chicken is white in the center, add pepper and pineapple, ginger and parsley.
Simmer.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 slices of waxed paper and pound with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Add green onions, lime, brandy, parsley and mustard to pan; cook 15 seconds.
Whisking constantly, add broth and remaining oil and butter.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Chop and saute onion in the 1/2 stick of butter.
Cook and drain spinach.
Drain and mash artichoke.
Mix spinach, artichoke and onion with all other ingredients except Jack cheese.
Put in baking dish and grate Jack cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla chips, sour cream and salsa.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients well in large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: orange dribble cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well at medium speed.
Pour in tube pan
and
bake
50 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Prick
holes
in
cake and pour Sauce over cake.
Let soak in and remove from pan.
Add icing to sides.

title: greek spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble the Feta with a fork. Drain spinach and mix with Feta and cottage cheese.
Mix the remaining ingredients and combine with the cheeses.
Pour into a well buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour or until knife comes clean with inserted in center.
Let cool a few minutes. Cut in squares to serve.
Serves 6.

title: prune crock
directions: Place prunes in a 2-quart glass jar.
Stir sugar and tea together in a saucepan.
Add remaining
ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over prunes and cover.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray baking pan.
Add soups and water and mix well.
Cover with rice.
Lay raw chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously grease (not oil) popover pans or deep custard cups.
In small bowl beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and beat just until blended.
(Do not overbeat.)
Fill prepared cups half full (about 1/3 cup) or batter.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Serve immediately.
If desired, serve from baking cups.
Makes 6 or 7 large popovers.

title: fritos pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Top with last 3 ingredients.
Very simple and D-Licious!

title: falafel (chickpea patties)
directions: Grind peas in meat grinder, or process in blender or food processor.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Form into approximately 20 balls.
Roll in flour to coat.
Flatten slightly. Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.

title: sweet potato or pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer and place in an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from broth and let cool, then debone it.
Dice it up and set aside.
Bring broth to a boil and take biscuits and pinch off bite size pieces and drop into boiling broth.
Be careful!
Continue boiling until dumplings are plump and soft, not gooey.
Turn down to a simmer and add your chicken, milk, salt and pepper.
Let simmer about 10 minutes. Stir well to keep dumplings from sticking.
If your dumplings are too thick, add more broth.
If they are too thin, add a couple tablespoons of cornstarch.

title: calico tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In greased 2-quart casserole, blend soup mix with milk.
Stir in macaroni, tuna, parsley and pimiento; top with bread crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes or until heated through.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar first.
Then add Cool Whip, pudding mix and milk.
Mix well and pour into cooled baked pie shell.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with shaved Hershey bard, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix well and pour into freezer pan.

title: cheese bake(great for breakfast)
directions: Butter bread, remove crusts and cut diagonally.
Put 4 slices in greased casserole.
Mix mustard with ham and spread over bread. Add half of cheese.
Cover with remaining bread slices and add rest of cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over the top.
Chill overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and chocolate. Cut in margarine until crumbly and dry.
Reserve 2 cups.
Press remainder firmly on bottom.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Pat meat evenly in bottom of baking dish.
Put onions over the meat, cheese slices over onions and sliced potatoes on top.
Pour mushroom soup over all.
Do not dilute soup.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: clam dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix mayonnaise thoroughly.
Add clams and juice.
Mix and add Worcestershire sauce to taste.

title: surprise apple salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let Jell-O thicken slightly. Add the apples, bananas and pineapple.
When well set, add topping.

title: chocolate crunch delight
directions: Melt all chips together in double boiler.
Add other ingredients and stir (gently fold) thoroughly.
Drop on waxed paper.
Allow to cool.

title: old favorite meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Put into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes around 10 servings.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Crumble and reserve.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in bacon drippings until tender.
Add ground beef, cook until well browned, breaking up with a fork as it cooks.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: raisin pie
directions: Barely cover raisins with water and 1/4 cup sugar in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook until raisins are plump and tender.
In separate bowl, mix flour and 1/3 cup sugar. Add 1/2 cup milk.
Mix well.
Gradually add remaining milk.
Add egg whites and mix.
Slowly add mix to raisins while they are still cooking.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Allow to cool a little, then add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: mushroom cream cheese rolls
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, salt and mushrooms.
Unroll crescent rolls, but do not split into triangles.
Pinch diagonal split in dough together.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins and save water they're cooked in.
Mix all ingredients except raisins.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: italian pasta primavera
directions: Saute onions, red pepper, broccoli and carrots for 5 minutes in hot olive oil.
Add zucchini and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes more. Add tomatoes and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over hot pasta. Vegetables should be seasoned when tomatoes are added.
Add basil, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper to taste.
Serves one.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except soda.
Bring to a boil, cook 2 1/2 minutes longer.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir well and remove from heat.
Pour over popped corn in a paper grocery bag that has been sprayed with Pam.
Shake really well.
Cook 2 1/2 minutes in microwave on High, stirring after 1 minute.
Add nuts and shake well.
Remove and spread on cookie sheet.
Crumble when cool.

title: broccoli casserole with stuffing
directions: Combine egg, onion, soup and mayo.
Layer cooked broccoli in 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer cheese and pour small amount of sauce.
Repeat layers until used up.
Put stuffing on top and pour butter over.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pecos pasta
directions: Prepare Creamettes elbow macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
In a large skillet melt butter; add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender (do not brown).
Add Hormel chili, corn, seasoned salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked Creamettes; top with shredded cheese. Cover and heat on low 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Bring peas and 3 quarts water to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. cover pan and let sit for 1 hour.
Cut up bacon and cook until brown; add onions and cook until golden.
Pour bacon mixture into peas.
Cover and simmer until peas are tender, about 1 hour.
Stir in rice and seasonings.
Cook, covered, without stirring, until rice is tender.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Microwave the cream cheese for 2 minutes.
Add the dressing and the crab meat; mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix and freeze.
Slice in thin slices and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: red cabbage with beer
directions: Fry the bacon, remove when crisp and drain on paper towels. Discard all but 2 tablespoons of bacon fat.
Saute onions and apple in bacon fat.
Transfer to a deep casserole and add shredded cabbage, red currant jelly, nutmeg, beer, salt and pepper; simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Serve with pork.
Serves 4.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix apples, pecans, celery and salt, then toss with mayonnaise.

title: japanese chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Place drumettes in single layer in baking dish.
Pour marinade over and coat drumettes well. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake chicken in marinade, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.
Serve warm or cold.
Only 60 calories each.
